97
00:05:53,410 --> 00:05:55,080
<i>- ♪ Remember me
- ♪ Remember me</i>

98
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:57,420
<i>♪ Each time you hear
a sad guitar</i>

99
00:05:57,420 --> 00:06:02,090
<i>♪ Know that I'm with you
the only way that I can be</i>

100
00:06:02,090 --> 00:06:06,090
<i>♪ Until you're
in my arms again ♪</i>

101
00:06:06,090 --> 00:06:08,910
MIGUEL: <i>He lived the kind
of life you dream about.</i>

102
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:14,310
<i>Until 1942.</i>

103
00:06:14,930 --> 00:06:16,000
(CLANGS)

104
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,250
<i>When he was crushed
by a giant bell.</i>

105
00:06:20,010 --> 00:06:22,720
<i>I want to be just like him.</i>

106
00:06:28,680 --> 00:06:30,880
<i>Sometimes,
I look at de la Cruz</i>

107
00:06:30,880 --> 00:06:35,120
<i>and I get this feeling
like we're connected.</i>

108
00:06:35,120 --> 00:06:40,070
<i>Like if he could play music,
maybe someday, I could too.</i>

109
00:06:40,730 --> 00:06:42,730
If it wasn't for my family.

110
00:06:42,730 --> 00:06:45,130
- <i>Ay-ay-ay, muchacho.</i>
- Huh?

111
00:06:45,130 --> 00:06:47,560
I asked for a shoe shine
not your life story.

112
00:06:47,570 --> 00:06:49,600
- Oh, yeah. Sorry.
- (STRUMS GUITAR)

113
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:52,870
I just can't really talk about
any of this at home. So...

114
00:06:52,870 --> 00:06:53,870
If I were you,

115
00:06:53,870 --> 00:06:56,040
I'd march right up
to my family and say...

116
00:06:56,040 --> 00:06:58,640
"Hey, I'm a musician.
Deal with it."

117
00:06:58,640 --> 00:07:00,580
I could never say that.

118
00:07:00,580 --> 00:07:02,110
You are a musician, no?

119
00:07:02,110 --> 00:07:03,510
(STAMMERS) I don't know.

120
00:07:03,520 --> 00:07:06,050
I mean, I only
really play for myself.

121
00:07:06,050 --> 00:07:09,120
Ah! Did de la Cruz become
the world's best musician

122
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:11,020
by hiding his skills?

123
00:07:11,020 --> 00:07:14,160
No! He walked out
onto that plaza

124
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:16,160
and he played out loud.

125
00:07:16,160 --> 00:07:18,630
<i>Mira, mira,</i> they're
setting up for tonight!

126
00:07:18,630 --> 00:07:21,030
The music competition
for <i>Dia de Muertos.</i>

127
00:07:21,030 --> 00:07:23,770
You want to be like your hero?
You should sign up!

128
00:07:23,770 --> 00:07:26,670
Uh-uh.
My family would freak!

129
00:07:26,670 --> 00:07:30,360
Look, if you're too scared then,
well, have fun making shoes.

130
00:07:31,140 --> 00:07:34,060
Come on, what did
de la Cruz always say?

131
00:07:34,210 --> 00:07:36,060
Seize your moment?

132
00:07:37,180 --> 00:07:39,180
Show me what
you got, <i>muchacho.</i>

133
00:07:39,180 --> 00:07:40,650
(GASPS)

134
00:07:40,650 --> 00:07:42,500
I'll be your first audience.

135
00:07:49,660 --> 00:07:51,240
- ABUELITA ELENA: Miguel!
- (GASPS)

136
00:07:52,930 --> 00:07:55,070
- <i>Abuelita!</i>
- What are you doing here?

137
00:07:55,070 --> 00:07:56,570
(MIGUEL STAMMERING)

138
00:07:56,570 --> 00:07:58,000
- You leave my grandson alone.
- (GROANS)

139
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,100
<i>Dona,</i> please!

140
00:07:59,110 --> 00:08:00,270
I was just getting
a shine. (GASPS)

141
00:08:00,270 --> 00:08:03,540
I know your tricks, mariachi.
What did he say to you?

142
00:08:03,540 --> 00:08:05,070
He was just
showing me his guitar.

143
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:06,880
- (BOTH GASP)
- Shame on you.

144
00:08:06,880 --> 00:08:12,180
My grandson is a sweet little
<i>angelito querido cielito.</i>

145
00:08:12,180 --> 00:08:14,920
He wants no part
of your music, mariachi.

146
00:08:14,920 --> 00:08:16,250
You keep away from him.

147
00:08:16,250 --> 00:08:18,140
(YELPING)

148
00:08:19,960 --> 00:08:23,690
<i>Ay, pobrecito.</i>
Oh, <i>estas bien, mijo.</i>

149
00:08:23,700 --> 00:08:25,700
(MUFFLED GROANING)

150
00:08:25,700 --> 00:08:27,930
You know better than to
be here in this place!

151
00:08:27,930 --> 00:08:31,320
You will come home. Now.

152
00:08:35,110 --> 00:08:37,160
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

153
00:08:41,350 --> 00:08:42,980
How many times
have we told you?

154
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:45,350
That plaza is
crawling with mariachis.

155
00:08:45,350 --> 00:08:47,580
- Yes, <i>Tio</i> Berto.
- (DANTE BARKING)

156
00:08:47,590 --> 00:08:50,720
- No, no, no, no, no!
- Ah! Go away, you. Go!

157
00:08:50,720 --> 00:08:51,990
- It's just Dante.
- (DANTE WHINES)

158
00:08:51,990 --> 00:08:54,120
Never name a street dog.

159
00:08:54,130 --> 00:08:57,180
They'll follow you forever.
Now, go get my shoe.

160
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:06,040
I found your son
in Mariachi Plaza.

161
00:09:06,040 --> 00:09:07,100
<i>Ay,</i> Miguel!

162
00:09:07,110 --> 00:09:09,740
You know how <i>Abuelita</i>
feels about the plaza.

163
00:09:09,740 --> 00:09:11,040
I was just shining shoes.

164
00:09:11,040 --> 00:09:12,610
A musician's shoes!

165
00:09:12,610 --> 00:09:14,280
(ALL GASP)

166
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:16,750
But the plaza's where
all the foot traffic is.

167
00:09:16,750 --> 00:09:20,380
If <i>Abuelita</i> says no more
plaza, then no more plaza.

168
00:09:20,390 --> 00:09:22,790
- But what about tonight?
- What's tonight?

169
00:09:22,790 --> 00:09:25,620
Well, they're having
this talent show.

170
00:09:25,620 --> 00:09:27,860
(STAMMERS) And I
thought I might...

171
00:09:27,860 --> 00:09:30,390
- Sign up?
- Well, maybe?

172
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:33,760
(LAUGHS) You have to have
talent to be in a talent show.

173
00:09:33,770 --> 00:09:36,730
What are you gonna do?
Shine shoes? (GROANS)

174
00:09:36,740 --> 00:09:38,200
It's <i>Dia de los Muertos.</i>

175
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:41,640
No one's going anywhere.
Tonight is about family.

176
00:09:41,640 --> 00:09:44,460
- (SPITS)
<i>- Ofrenda</i> room. <i>Vamonos.</i>

177
00:09:54,050 --> 00:09:55,190
- (KISSES)
- (SIGHS)

178
00:09:55,190 --> 00:09:57,050
Don't give me that look.

179
00:09:57,060 --> 00:09:59,890
<i>Dia de los Muertos</i>
is the one night of the year

180
00:09:59,890 --> 00:10:01,930
our ancestors
can come visit us.

181
00:10:01,930 --> 00:10:04,160
We've put their photos
on the <i>ofrenda</i>

182
00:10:04,160 --> 00:10:06,060
so their spirits
can cross over.

183
00:10:06,070 --> 00:10:08,030
That is very important.

184
00:10:08,030 --> 00:10:10,930
If we don't put them up,
they can't come.

185
00:10:10,940 --> 00:10:12,670
We made all this food,

186
00:10:12,670 --> 00:10:15,300
set out the things
they loved in life, <i>mijo.</i>

187
00:10:15,310 --> 00:10:18,670
All this work
to bring the family together.

188
00:10:18,680 --> 00:10:21,940
I don't want you sneaking
off to who knows where.

189
00:10:21,950 --> 00:10:23,380
(GASPS) Where are you going?

190
00:10:23,380 --> 00:10:24,920
(STAMMERS) I thought
we were done.

191
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:28,050
<i>Ay, Dios mio.</i> Being part
of this family means

192
00:10:28,050 --> 00:10:29,920
being here for this family.

193
00:10:29,920 --> 00:10:32,190
I don't want
to see you end up like...

194
00:10:32,190 --> 00:10:33,360
MIGUEL: Like <i>Mama</i> Coco's <i>papa?</i>

195
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:36,830
Never mention that man!
He's better off forgotten.

196
00:10:36,830 --> 00:10:37,930
- But you're the one who...
- (TUTTING)

197
00:10:37,930 --> 00:10:39,100
- I was just...
- (SHUSHING)

198
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:40,360
- But... I...
- (SHUSHING)

199
00:10:40,370 --> 00:10:43,730
<i>Papa? Papa</i> is home?

200
00:10:43,740 --> 00:10:46,700
<i>Mama, calmese, calmese.</i>

201
00:10:46,710 --> 00:10:48,470
<i>Papa</i> is coming home?

202
00:10:48,470 --> 00:10:51,590
No, <i>Mama.</i>
It's okay. I'm here.

203
00:10:52,710 --> 00:10:54,340
Who are you?

204
00:10:54,340 --> 00:10:57,950
(SIGHS) Rest, <i>Mama.</i>

205
00:10:57,950 --> 00:11:01,120
I'm hard on you
because I care, Miguel.

206
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:03,300
Miguel? Miguel?

207
00:11:04,260 --> 00:11:06,260
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

208
00:11:06,260 --> 00:11:09,390
What are we going
to do with that boy?

209
00:11:09,390 --> 00:11:13,450
(LAUGHS) You're right.
That's just what he needs.

210
00:11:15,270 --> 00:11:17,550
(GRUNTING)

211
