Other than you. Ew. Okay.

221
00:11:58,340 --> 00:12:00,490
- (STRUMS)
- <i>Perfecto!</i>

222
00:12:33,910 --> 00:12:36,480
<i>I have to sing.
I have to play!</i>

223
00:12:36,480 --> 00:12:41,230
<i>The music, it's not
just in me, it is me.</i>

224
00:12:41,850 --> 00:12:43,020
(STRUMMING GUITAR)

225
00:12:43,020 --> 00:12:46,140
<i>When life gets me down,
I play my guitar.</i>

226
00:12:47,060 --> 00:12:49,260
<i>The rest of the world
may follow the rules,</i>

227
00:12:49,260 --> 00:12:52,140
<i>but I must follow my heart.</i>

228
00:12:52,530 --> 00:12:54,200
Ugh!

229
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:57,000
<i>You know that feeling like
there's a song in the air and...</i>

230
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:59,120
<i>it's playing just for you?</i>

231
00:13:02,240 --> 00:13:05,410
<i>♪ A feeling so close...</i>

232
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:09,730
<i>♪ You could
reach out and touch it</i>

233
00:13:10,380 --> 00:13:12,250
<i>♪ I never knew</i>

234
00:13:12,250 --> 00:13:16,400
<i>♪ I could want something
so much, but it's true ♪</i>

235
00:13:17,360 --> 00:13:18,960
<i>You must have faith, sister.</i>

236
00:13:18,960 --> 00:13:21,390
<i>Oh, but,</i> Padre,
<i>he will never listen.</i>

237
00:13:21,390 --> 00:13:23,430
<i>He will listen. To music.</i>

238
00:13:23,430 --> 00:13:27,030
<i>♪ Only a song,
only a song</i>

239
00:13:27,030 --> 00:13:29,710
<i>♪ Has the power
to change a heart ♪</i>

240
00:13:33,970 --> 00:13:36,860
<i>Never underestimate
the power of music.</i>

241
00:13:41,250 --> 00:13:44,580
NUN: <i>But my father, he will
never give his permission.</i>

242
00:13:44,580 --> 00:13:46,220
DE LA CRUZ: <i>I am done
asking permission.</i>

243
00:13:46,220 --> 00:13:49,390
<i>When you see your moment, you
mustn't let it pass you by.</i>

244
00:13:49,390 --> 00:13:51,290
<i>You must seize it!</i>

245
00:13:51,290 --> 00:13:52,520
INTERVIEWER:
Senor <i>de la Cruz,</i>

246
00:13:52,520 --> 00:13:55,570
<i>what did it take for you
to seize your moment?</i>

247
00:13:57,130 --> 00:14:00,030
<i>I had to have
faith in my dream.</i>

248
00:14:00,030 --> 00:14:02,000
<i>No one was going
to hand it to me.</i>

249
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:04,300
<i>It was up to me
to reach for that dream.</i>

250
00:14:04,300 --> 00:14:06,270
<i>Grab it tight
and make it come true.</i>

251
00:14:06,270 --> 00:14:07,890
MIGUEL:
<i>...and make it come true.</i>

252
00:14:08,170 --> 00:14:09,890
(STATIC)

253
00:14:12,410 --> 00:14:16,050
No more hiding, Dante.
I got to seize my moment!

254
00:14:16,050 --> 00:14:17,210
(BARKS)

255
00:14:17,220 --> 00:14:20,220
I'm gonna play in Mariachi
Plaza if it kills me.

256
00:14:20,220 --> 00:14:22,900
- (BELL TOLLING)
- (CHILDREN LAUGHING)

257
00:14:23,590 --> 00:14:27,290
<i>Dia de los Muertos</i> has begun!

258
00:14:27,290 --> 00:14:30,560
No, no. We have to make
a clear path.

259
00:14:30,560 --> 00:14:33,200
The petals guide
our ancestors home.

260
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:35,230
We don't want
their spirits to get lost.

261
00:14:35,230 --> 00:14:37,940
We want them to come
and enjoy all the food

262
00:14:37,940 --> 00:14:39,550
and drinks on the <i>ofrenda.</i>

263
00:14:40,640 --> 00:14:42,000
- PAPA: <i>Mama!</i>
- (GASPS)

264
00:14:42,010 --> 00:14:43,370
Where should we
put this table?

265
00:14:43,370 --> 00:14:45,070
ABUELITA ELENA:
In the courtyard, <i>mijos.</i>

266
00:14:45,080 --> 00:14:46,240
PAPA: You want it
down by the kitchen?

267
00:14:46,250 --> 00:14:48,640
<i>Si.</i> Next to the other one.

268
00:14:48,650 --> 00:14:51,210
(PANTING)

269
00:14:51,220 --> 00:14:54,180
- Get under! Get under!
- Miguel?

270
00:14:54,190 --> 00:14:57,620
Nothing! <i>Mama, Papa.</i> I...

271
00:14:57,620 --> 00:15:02,490
Miguel, your <i>abuelita</i> had
the most wonderful idea.

272
00:15:02,490 --> 00:15:06,730
We've all decided. It's time
you joined us in the workshop!

273
00:15:06,730 --> 00:15:09,200
- What?
- No more shining shoes.

274
00:15:09,200 --> 00:15:12,140
You'll be making them
every day after school.

275
00:15:12,140 --> 00:15:15,200
Oh! Our Migueli-ti-ti-ti-to

276
00:15:15,210 --> 00:15:17,670
carrying on
the family tradition.

277
00:15:17,680 --> 00:15:20,340
And on <i>Dia de los Muertos!</i>

278
00:15:20,350 --> 00:15:23,150
Your ancestors
will be so proud.

279
00:15:23,150 --> 00:15:26,550
You'll craft huaraches
just like your <i>Tia</i> Victoria.

280
00:15:26,550 --> 00:15:29,220
PAPA: And wingtips
like your <i>Papa</i> Julio.

281
00:15:29,220 --> 00:15:31,750
(STAMMERS) But what if
I'm no good at making shoes?

282
00:15:31,760 --> 00:15:36,130
Ah, Miguel. You have your
family here to guide you.

283
00:15:36,130 --> 00:15:40,710
You are a Rivera.
And a Rivera is...

284
00:15:41,400 --> 00:15:44,270
A shoemaker.
Through and through.

285
00:15:44,270 --> 00:15:47,300
That's my boy!
(LAUGHS) Berto!

286
00:15:47,310 --> 00:15:50,270
Break out the good stuff.
I want to make a toast.

287
00:15:50,270 --> 00:15:53,180
- (KISSING)
- (GRUNTS)

288
00:15:53,180 --> 00:15:54,960
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

289
00:15:57,150 --> 00:15:58,710
- (SIGHS HEAVILY)
- (CLATTERS)

290
00:15:58,720 --> 00:16:00,180
(DANTE WHINES)

291
00:16:00,190 --> 00:16:03,900
Dante! No, Dante. Stop!

292
00:16:09,330 --> 00:16:10,560
(GASPS)

293
00:16:10,560 --> 00:16:12,010
(GRUNTING)

294
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:14,160
(GASPING)

295
00:16:14,170 --> 00:16:17,480
No, no, no, no, no! No.

296
00:16:25,340 --> 00:16:26,760
(GASPS)

297
00:16:29,310 --> 00:16:31,610
De la Cruz's guitar?

298
00:16:31,620 --> 00:16:35,070
<i>Papa? Papa?</i>

299
00:16:36,220 --> 00:16:40,190
<i>Mama</i> Coco, is your <i>papa</i>
Ernesto de la Cruz?

300
00:16:40,190 --> 00:16:42,830
<i>Papa! Papa!</i>

301
00:16:42,830 --> 00:16:44,680
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

302
00:16:52,770 --> 00:16:54,440
(LAUGHS)

303
00:16:54,440 --> 00:16:56,570
<i>Papa! Papa!</i> It's him!

304
00:16:56,580 --> 00:16:58,440
I know who my
great-great-grandfather was.

305
00:16:58,440 --> 00:17:00,480
Miguel, get down
from there.

306
00:17:00,480 --> 00:17:03,250
<i>Mama</i> Coco's father
was Ernesto de la Cruz!

307
00:17:03,250 --> 00:17:04,550
What are you talking about?

308
00:17:04,550 --> 00:17:06,630
I'm gonna be a musician!

309
00:17:08,350 --> 00:17:09,650
ABUELITA ELENA:
What is all this?

310
00:17:09,660 --> 00:17:11,750
You keep secrets
from your own family?

311
00:17:11,760 --> 00:17:14,090
It's all that time
he spends in the plaza.

312
00:17:14,090 --> 00:17:15,490
Fills his head
with crazy fantasies.

313
00:17:15,490 --> 00:17:17,090
It's not a fantasy.

314
00:17:17,100 --> 00:17:19,360
That man was
Ernesto de la Cruz!

315
00:17:19,360 --> 00:17:21,230
The greatest musician
of all time!

316
00:17:21,230 --> 00:17:22,770
We've never known anything
about this man!

317
00:17:22,770 --> 00:17:26,500
But whoever he was, he still
abandoned his family.

318
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:28,140
This is no future
for my son.

319
00:17:28,140 --> 00:17:30,670
But, <i>Papa,</i> you said
my family would guide me.

320
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:33,240
Well, de la Cruz
is my family.

321
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:34,780
I'm supposed to play music.

322
00:17:34,780 --> 00:17:37,110
Never! That man's music
was a curse.

323
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:39,120
I will not allow it.

324
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:40,650
- If you would just let...
- Miguel...

325
00:17:40,650 --> 00:17:42,250
You will listen
to your family.

326
00:17:42,250 --> 00:17:43,550
No more music.

327
00:17:43,550 --> 00:17:46,700
- Just listen to me play!
- End of argument.

328
00:17:47,190 --> 00:17:48,520
(STRUMMING)

329
00:17:48,530 --> 00:17:51,190
You want to end up
like that man? Forgotten?

330
00:17:51,200 --> 00:17:53,600
Left off
your family's <i>ofrenda?</i>

331
00:17:53,600 --> 00:17:55,730
I don't care if I'm on
some stupid <i>ofrenda.</i>

332
00:17:55,730 --> 00:17:57,620
(ALL GASP)

333
00:17:58,500 --> 00:17:59,570
(GRUNTS)

334
00:17:59,570 --> 00:18:00,740
- No!
- <i>Mama!</i>

335
00:18:00,740 --> 00:18:02,650
(GRUNTING)

336
00:18:03,740 --> 00:18:05,440
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

337
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:09,280
There. No guitar.
No music.

338
00:18:09,280 --> 00:18:11,550
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

339
00:18:11,550 --> 00:18:16,480
Oh, come. You'll feel better
after you eat with your family.

340
00:18:16,490 --> 00:18:18,600
I don't want
to be in this family!

341
00:18:18,820 --> 00:18:21,070
Miguel! Miguel!

342
00:18:23,830 --> 00:18:25,740
(PANTING)

343
00:18:28,430 --> 00:18:29,880
(YIPPING)

344
00:18:37,180 --> 00:18:39,510
(MAN SINGING IN SPANISH)

345
00:18:39,510 --> 00:18:42,380
I want to play in the plaza,
like de la Cruz.

346
00:18:42,380 --> 00:18:43,580
Can I still sign up?

347
00:18:43,580 --> 00:18:45,250
You got an instrument?

348
00:18:45,250 --> 00:18:47,580
(STAMMERS) No. But if I
can borrow a guitar...

349
00:18:47,590 --> 00:18:49,450
Musicians got to bring
their own instruments.

350
00:18:49,450 --> 00:18:50,920
- (CROWD CHEERING)
- You find a guitar, kid,

351
00:18:50,920 --> 00:18:52,640
I'll put you on the list.

352
00:18:54,860 --> 00:18:58,330
- Can I borrow your guitar?
- Sorry, <i>muchacho.</i>

353
00:18:58,330 --> 00:19:01,330
- You guys have a spare guitar?
- No.

354
00:19:01,330 --> 00:19:03,470
I need a guitar
just for a little bit.

355
00:19:03,470 --> 00:19:06,050
- Get out of here, kid.
- (SIGHS)

356
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:17,880
(FIREWORKS EXPLODING)

357
00:19:17,880 --> 00:19:22,230
Great-great-grandfather,
what am I supposed to do?

358
00:19:59,930 --> 00:20:01,420
- (BARKS)
- No, no, no, no.

359
00:20:01,430 --> 00:20:04,290
Dante, stop! <i>Callate!</i> Shh!

360
00:20:04,300 --> 00:20:06,240
(CONTINUES BARKING)

361
00:20:06,530 --> 00:20:07,980
(GRUNTS)

362
00:20:16,670 --> 00:20:19,120
(FIREWORKS CONTINUE
EXPLODING)

363
00:20:25,750 --> 00:20:27,270
I'm sorry.

364
00:20:27,590 --> 00:20:28,900
(GLASS SHATTERS)

365
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:45,650
- (STONE SHIFTS)
- (GASPS)

366
00:21:03,520 --> 00:21:07,360
<i>Senor</i> de la Cruz,
please don't be mad.

367
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:08,720
(STAMMERS) I'm Miguel.

368
00:21:08,730 --> 00:21:13,310
Your great-great grandson.
I need to borrow this.

369
00:21:16,330 --> 00:21:18,870
(SIGHS) Our family thinks
music is a curse.

370
00:21:18,870 --> 00:21:22,770
None of them understand
but I know you would have.

371
00:21:22,770 --> 00:21:25,540
You would have told me
to follow my heart.

372
00:21:25,540 --> 00:21:27,060
To seize my moment!

373
00:21:28,350 --> 00:21:31,350
So, if it's
all right with you,

374
00:21:31,350 --> 00:21:34,070
I'm gonna play in the plaza.
Just like you did!

375
00:21:35,550 --> 00:21:37,600
(STRUMS GUITAR)

376
00:21:41,790 --> 00:21:44,760
- MAN 1: The guitar! It's gone!
- (GASPING)

377
00:21:44,760 --> 00:21:47,060
MAN 2: Somebody stole
de la Cruz's guitar!

378
00:21:47,060 --> 00:21:49,370
WOMAN: The window's broken.
Look!

379
00:21:49,370 --> 00:21:51,980
- (PANTING)
- (KEYS JANGLING)

380
00:21:53,770 --> 00:21:55,540
All right, who's in there?

381
00:21:55,540 --> 00:21:57,370
I'm sorry.
It's not what it looks like.

382
00:21:57,380 --> 00:21:58,890
De la Cruz is my...

383
00:21:59,980 --> 00:22:02,260
- (GASPS)
- There's nobody here.

384
00:22:02,910 --> 00:22:05,730
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

385
00:22:06,390 --> 00:22:08,700
(GASPING)

386
00:22:17,700 --> 00:22:19,060
- MAMA: Miguel!
- <i>Mama!</i>

387
00:22:19,060 --> 00:22:23,700
Miguel, come home.
Where are you, Miguel?

388
00:22:23,700 --> 00:22:24,800
(YELPING)

389
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:26,940
(GROANS)

390
00:22:26,940 --> 00:22:30,540
<i>Dios mio!</i>
Little boy. Are you okay?

391
00:22:30,540 --> 00:22:32,260
Here. Let me help you.

392
00:22:33,150 --> 00:22:34,930
Thanks. I...

393
00:22:35,410 --> 00:22:37,260
(BOTH SCREAMING)

394
00:22:38,080 --> 00:22:39,900
(RATTLING)

395
00:22:40,420 --> 00:22:41,800
(YELPING)

396
00:22:45,120 --> 00:22:47,440
- Do you mind? Whoa!
- (YELPS)

397
00:22:48,460 --> 00:22:50,270
- (PANTING)
- (INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

398
00:22:58,970 --> 00:23:01,320
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

399
00:23:02,170 --> 00:23:04,160
(BOTH LAUGHING)

400
00:23:07,980 --> 00:23:10,710
- Look how big she's getting.
- (CHUCKLES)

401
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:13,850
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

402
00:23:13,850 --> 00:23:15,750
(GASPS) Dante!

403
00:23:15,750 --> 00:23:18,750
- You can see me? Wait!
- (BARKING)

404
00:23:18,760 --> 00:23:21,810
What's going on? Dante!

405
00:23:22,760 --> 00:23:23,690
(BOTH GRUNT)

406
00:23:23,700 --> 00:23:25,990
- Oh, I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
- Miguel?

407
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:27,780
- Miguel?
- Miguel?

408
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,310
(GASPS)

409
00:23:31,170 --> 00:23:34,870
You're here? Here, here.
And you can see us?

410
00:23:34,870 --> 00:23:37,510
- Our Migueli-ti-ti-ti-to!
- (YELPING)

411
00:23:37,510 --> 00:23:39,010
Remind me how I know you.

412
00:23:39,010 --> 00:23:41,990
- We're your family, <i>mijo.</i>
- (GASPING)

413
00:23:42,950 --> 00:23:45,800
- MIGUEL: <i>Tia</i> Rosita?
<i>- Si.</i>

414
00:23:47,690 --> 00:23:49,970
- MIGUEL: <i>Papa</i> Julio?
<i>- Hola.</i>

415
00:23:50,720 --> 00:23:52,160
MIGUEL: <i>Tia</i> Victoria?

416
00:23:52,160 --> 00:23:54,660
He doesn't
seem entirely dead.

417
00:23:54,660 --> 00:23:57,560
- (GRUNTS)
- He's not quite alive either.

418
00:23:57,560 --> 00:24:00,160
We need <i>Mama</i> Imelda.
She'll know how to fix this.

419
00:24:00,170 --> 00:24:04,170
<i>Oye!</i> It's <i>Mama</i> Imelda.

420
00:24:04,170 --> 00:24:05,570
- She couldn't cross over.
- (ALL GASP)

421
00:24:05,570 --> 00:24:08,000
- She's stuck!
- On the other side!

422
00:24:08,010 --> 00:24:10,810
<i>Tio</i> Oscar? <i>Tio</i> Felipe?

423
00:24:10,810 --> 00:24:12,910
- Oh. Hey, Miguel.
- (BOTH GASP)

424
00:24:12,910 --> 00:24:15,540
I have a feeling this has
something to do with you.

425
00:24:15,550 --> 00:24:17,680
But if <i>Mama</i> Imelda
can't come to us...

426
00:24:17,680 --> 00:24:19,950
Then we are going to her.
<i>Vamonos!</i>

427
00:24:19,950 --> 00:24:22,130
(DANTE BARKING)

428
00:24:23,850 --> 00:24:25,170
(GASPS)

429
00:24:33,860 --> 00:24:35,230
Whoa.

430
00:24:35,230 --> 00:24:37,980
Come on, Miguel.
It's okay.

431
00:24:39,670 --> 00:24:41,120
(DANTE BARKS)

432
00:24:48,550 --> 00:24:50,680
(DANTE CONTINUES BARKING)

433
00:24:50,680 --> 00:24:55,170
Dante? Dante!
Dante, wait up!

434
00:24:57,590 --> 00:25:02,440
You got to stay with me, boy.
We don't know... where...

435
00:25:22,850 --> 00:25:26,280
This isn't a dream then.
You're all really out there.

436
00:25:26,280 --> 00:25:28,250
- You thought we weren't?
- Well, I don't know.

437
00:25:28,250 --> 00:25:30,120
I thought it might've been
one of those

438
00:25:30,120 --> 00:25:32,050
made up things
that adults tell kids.

439
00:25:32,060 --> 00:25:33,620
Like vitamins.

440
00:25:33,630 --> 00:25:35,760
Miguel,
vitamins are a real thing.

441
00:25:35,760 --> 00:25:37,930
Well, now I'm thinking
maybe they could be.

442
00:25:37,930 --> 00:25:40,000
- (GASPS)
- <i>Mija,</i> it's not nice to stare at...

443
00:25:40,000 --> 00:25:41,660
<i>Ay!</i> Santa Maria!

444
00:25:41,670 --> 00:25:43,080
(WHOOSHING)

445
00:25:49,340 --> 00:25:53,740
Are those...
Alebrijes! But those are...

446
00:25:53,750 --> 00:25:56,280
OSCAR: Real alebrijes.
Spirit creatures.

447
00:25:56,280 --> 00:25:58,150
They guide souls
on their journey.

448
00:25:58,150 --> 00:26:00,620
Watch your step. They
make <i>caquitas</i> everywhere.

449
00:26:00,620 --> 00:26:02,820
ANNOUNCER: <i>Welcome back
to the Land of the Dead.</i>

450
00:26:02,820 --> 00:26:05,660
<i>Please have all offerings
ready for re-entry.</i>

451
00:26:05,660 --> 00:26:07,890
Welcome back.
Anything to declare?

452
00:26:07,890 --> 00:26:09,360
Some churros.
From my family.

453
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:11,360
ARRIVALS AGENT:
How wonderful. Next.

454
00:26:11,360 --> 00:26:13,230
ANNOUNCER: <i>If you are
experiencing travel issues,</i>

455
00:26:13,230 --> 00:26:14,960
<i>agents at
the Department of Family...</i>

456
00:26:14,970 --> 00:26:17,200
<i>Reunions are
available to assist you.</i>

457
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:18,980
DEPARTURES AGENT:
Next family, please.

458
00:26:21,370 --> 00:26:22,470
(DINGS)

459
00:26:22,470 --> 00:26:25,040
Oh! Your photos
are on your son's <i>ofrenda.</i>

460
00:26:25,040 --> 00:26:26,410
Have a great visit.

461
00:26:26,410 --> 00:26:27,680
BOTH: <i>Gracias.</i>

462
00:26:27,680 --> 00:26:29,710
ANNOUNCER: <i>And remember
to return before sunrise.</i>

463
00:26:29,710 --> 00:26:30,910
<i>Enjoy your visit.</i>

464
00:26:30,920 --> 00:26:33,250
- Next.
- (DINGS)

465
00:26:33,250 --> 00:26:36,790
Your photo's on your dentist's <i>ofrenda.</i>
Enjoy your visit.

466
00:26:36,790 --> 00:26:38,570
- <i>Gracias.</i>
- Next?

467
00:26:40,860 --> 00:26:43,090
Yes! It is I.
Frida Kahlo.

468
00:26:43,090 --> 00:26:44,660
Shall we skip
the scanner?

469
00:26:44,660 --> 00:26:48,380
I'm on so many <i>ofrendas</i> it'll just
overwhelm your blinky thingy.

470
00:26:48,930 --> 00:26:50,100
(BUZZING)

471
00:26:50,100 --> 00:26:54,670
Well, shoot, looks like no one
put up your photo, Frida.

472
00:26:54,670 --> 00:26:58,940
Okay, when I said I was Frida,
just now, that was a lie.

473
00:26:58,940 --> 00:27:00,340
And I apologize
for doing that.

474
00:27:00,340 --> 00:27:03,210
No photo on an <i>ofrenda,</i>
no crossing the bridge.

475
00:27:03,210 --> 00:27:07,000
I'm just gonna zip right over.
You won't even know I'm gone.

476
00:27:07,950 --> 00:27:10,130
- Hey!
- (LAUGHS)

477
00:27:10,750 --> 00:27:12,070
(WOMAN YELPS)

478
00:27:12,960 --> 00:27:14,570
(PANTING)

479
00:27:15,690 --> 00:27:19,430
Almost... there.
Just a little further.

480
00:27:19,430 --> 00:27:21,280
(PANTING)

481
00:27:22,300 --> 00:27:23,680
(SIGHS)

482
00:27:24,240 --> 00:27:25,300
Upsy-daisy...

483
00:27:25,300 --> 00:27:29,700
Fine. Okay. Fine, who cares?
Dumb flower bridge!

484
00:27:29,710 --> 00:27:33,810
Aw. I don't know what I'd do
if no one put up my photo.

485
00:27:33,810 --> 00:27:36,110
- ARRIVALS AGENT: Next?
- Oh! Come, <i>mijo.</i> It's our turn.

486
00:27:36,110 --> 00:27:39,050
Welcome back, <i>amigos.</i>
Anything to declare?

487
00:27:39,050 --> 00:27:42,470
As a matter of fact, yes.
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

488
00:27:42,850 --> 00:27:44,170
<i>Hola.</i>

489
00:27:50,990 --> 00:27:53,160
MALE ANNOUNCER:
<i>Paging Marta Gonzales-Ramos.</i>

490
00:27:53,160 --> 00:27:56,050
<i>Please report to Level Seven.</i>

491
00:28:00,340 --> 00:28:02,090
MIGUEL: Whoa!

492
00:28:02,440 --> 00:28:03,750
(ALL GASP)

493
00:28:05,280 --> 00:28:07,320
(SIGHS) I miss my nose.

494
00:28:12,450 --> 00:28:14,600
(INDISTINCT CHATTERING)

495
00:28:16,350 --> 00:28:18,320
Come on, help us out, <i>amigo.</i>

496
00:28:18,320 --> 00:28:19,790
We got to get to
a dozen <i>ofrendas</i> tonight.

497
00:28:19,790 --> 00:28:23,930
We are not visiting your ex-wife's
family for <i>Dia de Muertos!</i>

498
00:28:23,930 --> 00:28:26,460
I demand to speak
to the person in charge!

499
00:28:26,460 --> 00:28:29,370
I'm sorry, <i>senora,</i> it says
here no one put up your photo.

500
00:28:29,370 --> 00:28:33,940
My family always puts my
photo on the <i>ofrenda.</i>

501
00:28:33,940 --> 00:28:37,040
That devil box tells
you nothing but lies!

502
00:28:37,040 --> 00:28:41,810
- <i>Mama</i> Imelda? (GASPS)
- Oh, <i>mi familia!</i>

503
00:28:41,810 --> 00:28:43,410
They wouldn't let me
cross the bridge.

504
00:28:43,410 --> 00:28:45,920
Tell this woman
and her devil box

505
00:28:45,920 --> 00:28:48,450
that my photo
is on the <i>ofrenda.</i>

506
00:28:48,450 --> 00:28:51,920
(STAMMERS) Well, we never
made it to the <i>ofrenda.</i>

507
00:28:51,920 --> 00:28:55,640
- What?
- We ran into... (STAMMERS)

508
00:28:58,330 --> 00:29:01,450
- (GASPS) Miguel?
- <i>Mama</i> Imelda.

509
00:29:01,870 --> 00:29:04,200
What is going on?

510
00:29:04,200 --> 00:29:06,500
You the Rivera family?

511
00:29:06,500 --> 00:29:08,100
(COMPUTER EXPLODES)

512
00:29:08,110 --> 00:29:09,470
Well, you're cursed.

513
00:29:09,470 --> 00:29:10,610
- (ALL GASP)
- What?

514
00:29:10,610 --> 00:29:13,240
<i>Dia de los Muertos</i> is the
night to give to the dead.

515
00:29:13,240 --> 00:29:14,840
You stole from the dead!

516
00:29:14,850 --> 00:29:16,210
But I wasn't
stealing the guitar.

517
00:29:16,210 --> 00:29:17,350
Guitar?

518
00:29:17,350 --> 00:29:18,950
It was my
great-great-grandfather's.

519
00:29:18,950 --> 00:29:20,250
He would have
wanted me to have it.

520
00:29:20,250 --> 00:29:23,390
Ah, ah, ah. We do not speak
of that musician.

521
00:29:23,390 --> 00:29:25,120
He is dead to this family.

522
00:29:25,120 --> 00:29:27,090
MIGUEL: Uh,
you're all dead.

523
00:29:27,090 --> 00:29:28,160
(SNEEZES)

524
00:29:28,160 --> 00:29:30,830
I am sorry.
Whose alebrije is that?

525
00:29:30,830 --> 00:29:32,090
That's just Dante.

526
00:29:32,100 --> 00:29:34,230
He sure doesn't
look like an alebrije.

527
00:29:34,230 --> 00:29:35,830
He just looks
like a plain old dog.

528
00:29:35,830 --> 00:29:38,100
Or a sausage someone dropped
in a barbershop.

529
00:29:38,100 --> 00:29:41,870
Whatever he is, I am
(SNEEZES) terribly allergic.

530
00:29:41,870 --> 00:29:43,540
But Dante
doesn't have any hair.

531
00:29:43,540 --> 00:29:46,240
And I don't have a nose,
and yet, here we are.

532
00:29:46,240 --> 00:29:47,440
(SNEEZES)

533
00:29:47,450 --> 00:29:51,150
But none of this explains
why I couldn't cross over.

534
00:29:51,150 --> 00:29:52,830
Oh! (CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

535
00:29:53,120 --> 00:29:54,280
(ALL GASP)

536
00:29:54,280 --> 00:29:57,020
You took my photo
off the <i>ofrenda?</i>

537
00:29:57,020 --> 00:29:59,120
- It was an accident!
- How do we send him back?

538
00:29:59,120 --> 00:30:01,860
(CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY) Well,
since it's a family matter...

539
00:30:01,860 --> 00:30:04,290
the way to undo
a family curse

540
00:30:04,290 --> 00:30:07,030
- is to get your family's blessing.
- That's it?

541
00:30:07,030 --> 00:30:08,430
Get your family's blessing

542
00:30:08,430 --> 00:30:11,030
and everything should
go back to normal.

543
00:30:11,030 --> 00:30:13,070
But you got
to do it by sunrise.

544
00:30:13,070 --> 00:30:15,000
(STAMMERS)
What happens at sunrise?

545
00:30:15,010 --> 00:30:16,860
<i>Hijole!</i> Your hand!

546
00:30:17,480 --> 00:30:18,790
(GASPS)

547
00:30:21,010 --> 00:30:22,010
(GROANS)

548
00:30:22,010 --> 00:30:24,880
Whoa, Miguel, can't have
you fainting on us.

549
00:30:24,880 --> 00:30:27,450
(CHUCKLES) But not to worry.
Your family's here.

550
00:30:27,450 --> 00:30:29,480
You can get
your blessing right now.

551
00:30:29,490 --> 00:30:34,460
<i>Cempasuchil, cempasuchil.</i>
Aha! <i>Perdon, senora.</i>

552
00:30:34,460 --> 00:30:35,420
Oh. (GIGGLES)

553
00:30:35,430 --> 00:30:38,340
Now, you look at the living
and say his name.

554
00:30:39,230 --> 00:30:40,260
Miguel.

555
00:30:40,260 --> 00:30:43,570
Nailed it. Now say,
"I give you my blessing."

556
00:30:43,570 --> 00:30:45,620
I give you my blessing.

557
00:30:48,040 --> 00:30:51,440
I give you my blessing
to go home...

558
00:30:51,440 --> 00:30:54,610
to put my photo
back on the <i>ofrenda,</i>

559
00:30:54,610 --> 00:30:57,050
and to never
play music again.

560
00:30:57,050 --> 00:30:58,920
What? She can't do that!

561
00:30:58,920 --> 00:31:02,180
Well, technically, she can
add any condition she wants.

562
00:31:02,190 --> 00:31:04,320
(SIGHS) Fine.

563
00:31:04,320 --> 00:31:06,540
CLERK: Then you hand
the petal to Miguel.

564
00:31:12,330 --> 00:31:14,190
(GASPS)

565
00:31:14,200 --> 00:31:15,650
(LAUGHS IN RELIEF)

566
00:31:19,070 --> 00:31:20,420
No skeletons!

567
00:31:20,970 --> 00:31:22,520
(LAUGHS)

568
00:31:24,510 --> 00:31:26,790
Mariachi Plaza,
here I come.

569
00:31:27,950 --> 00:31:29,530
(GRUNTS)

570
00:31:31,010 --> 00:31:33,210
Two seconds and you already
break your promise.

571
00:31:33,220 --> 00:31:37,090
This isn't fair. It's my life.
You already had yours.

572
00:31:37,090 --> 00:31:39,160
<i>Papa</i> Julio,
I ask for your blessing.

573
00:31:39,160 --> 00:31:42,260
- (WHIMPERS)
- <i>Tia</i> Rosita? Oscar?

574
00:31:42,260 --> 00:31:45,130
- (ALL WHIMPERING)
- Felipe? <i>Tia</i> Victoria?

575
00:31:45,130 --> 00:31:49,530
Don't make this hard, <i>mijo.</i>
You go home my way or no way.

576
00:31:49,530 --> 00:31:51,400
You really hate
music that much?

577
00:31:51,400 --> 00:31:54,550
I will not let you go down
the same path he did.

578
00:31:56,980 --> 00:32:01,180
The same path he did.
He's family.

579
00:32:01,180 --> 00:32:02,980
Listen to your <i>Mama</i> Imelda.

580
00:32:02,980 --> 00:32:04,250
She's just
looking out for you.

581
00:32:04,250 --> 00:32:05,310
Be reasonable.

582
00:32:05,320 --> 00:32:08,650
<i>Con permiso,</i>
I need to visit the restroom.

583
00:32:08,650 --> 00:32:10,430
Be right back.

584
00:32:11,290 --> 00:32:13,390
Uh, should we tell him
there are no restrooms

585
00:32:13,390 --> 00:32:14,710
in the Land of the Dead?

586
00:32:15,290 --> 00:32:16,870
(PANTING)

587
00:32:23,300 --> 00:32:24,720
(GASPS)

588
00:32:27,740 --> 00:32:28,910
<i>Vamonos.</i>

589
00:32:28,910 --> 00:32:31,610
PATROLWOMAN: We got a family
looking for a living boy.

590
00:32:31,610 --> 00:32:34,340
If I want to be a musician,
I need a musician's blessing.

591
00:32:34,340 --> 00:32:36,410
We got to find
my great-great-grandpa.

592
00:32:36,410 --> 00:32:38,460
- Hold it, <i>muchacho.</i>
- (GASPS)

593
00:32:40,490 --> 00:32:42,050
(SHOUTS)

594
00:32:42,050 --> 00:32:43,420
I found that living boy!

595
00:32:43,420 --> 00:32:45,650
Oh, whoa, excuse me.
Excuse me, folks.

596
00:32:45,660 --> 00:32:47,010
Excuse me.

597
00:32:47,760 --> 00:32:49,270
Oh.

598
00:32:53,030 --> 00:32:55,300
No, no. Dante!

599
00:32:55,300 --> 00:32:58,330
Disturbing the peace.
Fleeing an officer.

600
00:32:58,340 --> 00:33:00,200
Falsifying a unibrow.

601
00:33:00,200 --> 00:33:02,470
- That's illegal?
- Very illegal.

602
00:33:02,470 --> 00:33:04,570
You need to clean up
your act, <i>amigo.</i>

603
00:33:04,570 --> 00:33:08,310
<i>Amigo?</i> Oh, that's so nice
to hear you say that

604
00:33:08,310 --> 00:33:10,110
because I have just had a...

605
00:33:10,110 --> 00:33:13,050
really hard <i>Dia de Muertos</i>
and I could really use

606
00:33:13,050 --> 00:33:14,050
- an <i>amigo</i> right now.
- (SIGHS)

607
00:33:14,050 --> 00:33:16,790
And <i>amigos,</i>
they help their <i>amigos.</i>

608
00:33:16,790 --> 00:33:19,490
You get me across
that bridge tonight,

609
00:33:19,490 --> 00:33:21,090
and I'll make it
worth your while.

610
00:33:21,090 --> 00:33:24,190
Oh! You like de la Cruz?
He and I go way back.

611
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:27,530
I can get you front row seats to
his Sunrise Spectacular show.

612
00:33:27,530 --> 00:33:29,730
I'll get you backstage.
You can meet him.

613
00:33:29,730 --> 00:33:31,470
You just got to let me
cross that bridge!

614
00:33:31,470 --> 00:33:33,640
I should lock you up
for the rest of the holiday.

615
00:33:33,640 --> 00:33:37,740
But my shift's almost up and I
want to visit my living family.

616
00:33:37,740 --> 00:33:40,460
So I'm letting you off
with a warning.

617
00:33:41,410 --> 00:33:43,550
Can I at least
get my costume back?

618
00:33:43,550 --> 00:33:45,350
Uh... No.

619
00:33:45,350 --> 00:33:47,830
(GROANS) Some <i>amigo.</i>

620
00:33:50,290 --> 00:33:53,760
Hey! Hey!
You really know de la Cruz?

621
00:33:53,760 --> 00:33:56,390
Who wants to... Ahh!
<i>Ay!</i> You're alive!

622
00:33:56,390 --> 00:33:58,090
Shh! Yeah, I'm alive.

623
00:33:58,100 --> 00:34:00,160
And if I want to get back
to the Land of the Living...

624
00:34:00,160 --> 00:34:01,630
I need de la Cruz's blessing.

625
00:34:01,630 --> 00:34:03,230
That's weirdly specific.

626
00:34:03,230 --> 00:34:04,770
He's my
great-great-grandfather.

627
00:34:04,770 --> 00:34:07,350
(STAMMERING)
He's your Gr... What?

628
00:34:07,770 --> 00:34:09,700
Ugh.

629
00:34:09,710 --> 00:34:13,560
Wait, wait, wait.
Wait, wait. (GASPS)

630
00:34:14,410 --> 00:34:16,510
Wait. No, wait, wait, wait.

631
00:34:16,510 --> 00:34:20,650
Wait! Yes! You're going back
to the Land of the Living!

632
00:34:20,650 --> 00:34:22,650
You know what? Maybe this
isn't such a good...

633
00:34:22,650 --> 00:34:25,390
No, no, <i>nino! Nino, nino,</i> I can help you.
You can help me.

634
00:34:25,390 --> 00:34:26,520
We can help each other.

635
00:34:26,520 --> 00:34:28,390
But most importantly,
you can help me.

636
00:34:28,390 --> 00:34:29,890
- Miguel!
- I'm Hector.

637
00:34:29,890 --> 00:34:31,440
- That's nice.
- (YELPS)

638
00:34:36,130 --> 00:34:37,780
<i>Esperame, chamaco!</i>

639
00:34:43,740 --> 00:34:45,610
(ALL GRUNTING)

640
00:34:45,610 --> 00:34:48,180
<i>Ay,</i> he is going
to get himself killed.

641
00:34:48,180 --> 00:34:51,800
I need my spirit guide...
Pepita. (WHISTLES)

642
00:34:52,220 --> 00:34:54,530
(SCREECHING)

643
00:35:03,490 --> 00:35:05,560
Who has that petal
Miguel touched?

644
00:35:05,560 --> 00:35:08,680
- (GROWLING)
- Here. Nice alebrije.

645
00:35:08,730 --> 00:35:10,050
(GASPS)

646
00:35:10,700 --> 00:35:12,950
(SNIFFING)

647
00:35:14,740 --> 00:35:16,550
(SNARLING)

648
00:35:20,180 --> 00:35:21,710
(CLATTERS)

649
00:35:21,710 --> 00:35:26,030
<i>Ay, ay,</i> hold still. Look up. <i>A ver, a ver.</i>
Look up, up, up.

650
00:35:26,320 --> 00:35:27,320
(SNIFFING)

651
00:35:27,320 --> 00:35:32,450
<i>Aqui arriba, eso...</i>
Eh, <i>la rayita.</i>

652
00:35:32,460 --> 00:35:35,040
Okay. Hey! Ta-da!

653
00:35:35,730 --> 00:35:37,580
Dead as a doorknob.

654
00:35:38,530 --> 00:35:41,630
So listen, Miguel,
this place runs on memories.

655
00:35:41,630 --> 00:35:42,860
When you're well remembered,

656
00:35:42,870 --> 00:35:44,730
people put up your photo
and you get to...

657
00:35:44,730 --> 00:35:46,330
cross the bridge
and visit the living

658
00:35:46,340 --> 00:35:48,800
on <i>Dia de Muertos.</i>
Unless you're me.

659
00:35:48,810 --> 00:35:50,610
You don't get
to cross over?

660
00:35:50,610 --> 00:35:51,870
No one's ever
put up my picture.

661
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:53,660
But you can change that!

662
00:35:53,880 --> 00:35:55,640
MIGUEL: This is you?

663
00:35:55,650 --> 00:35:57,280
Eh, <i>muy guapo,</i> eh?

664
00:35:57,280 --> 00:36:00,380
So, you get me
to my great-great-grandpa...

665
00:36:00,380 --> 00:36:03,280
then I put up your photo
when I get home?

666
00:36:03,290 --> 00:36:06,960
Such a smart boy! Yes!
Great idea, yes! One hiccup.

667
00:36:06,960 --> 00:36:08,890
De la Cruz is
a tough guy to get to

668
00:36:08,890 --> 00:36:10,690
and I need to
cross the bridge soon.

669
00:36:10,690 --> 00:36:11,690
Like, tonight.

670
00:36:11,700 --> 00:36:13,660
So, you got any other
family here, you know?

671
00:36:13,660 --> 00:36:15,800
Someone a bit more,
eh, accessible?

672
00:36:15,800 --> 00:36:17,630
Mmm... Nope.

673
00:36:17,630 --> 00:36:18,970
Don't yank my chain,
<i>chamaco.</i>

674
00:36:18,970 --> 00:36:20,570
You got to have
some other family.

675
00:36:20,570 --> 00:36:21,900
Only de la Cruz.

676
00:36:21,910 --> 00:36:23,940
If you can't help me,
I'll find him myself.

677
00:36:23,940 --> 00:36:25,370
(MIGUEL WHISTLES)

678
00:36:25,370 --> 00:36:27,810
Oh! Okay. Okay, kid.
Fine! Fine!

679
00:36:27,810 --> 00:36:29,690
I'll get you to your
great-great-grandpa.

680
00:36:31,380 --> 00:36:32,850
It's not gonna
be easy, you know?

681
00:36:32,850 --> 00:36:35,990
He's a busy man.
What are you doing?

682
00:36:35,990 --> 00:36:38,650
I'm walking like a skeleton.
Blending in.

683
00:36:38,660 --> 00:36:40,460
No. Skeletons
don't walk like that.

684
00:36:40,460 --> 00:36:44,530
- It's how you walk.
- No, I don't! Stop it!

685
00:36:44,530 --> 00:36:48,460
Whoa! Ernesto de la Cruz's
Sunrise Spectacular?

686
00:36:48,470 --> 00:36:50,270
- <i>Que padre!</i>
- (SCOFFS)

687
00:36:50,270 --> 00:36:53,400
Every year your great-great-grandpa
puts on that dumb show...

688
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:54,840
to mark the end
of <i>Dia de Muertos.</i>

689
00:36:54,840 --> 00:36:57,410
- And you can get us in!
- Um...

690
00:36:57,410 --> 00:36:59,670
Hey, you said you have
front row tickets!

691
00:36:59,680 --> 00:37:02,880
That... was a lie.
I apologize for that.

692
00:37:02,880 --> 00:37:05,050
Cool off, <i>chamaco.</i>
Come on. I'll get you to him.

693
00:37:05,050 --> 00:37:06,150
How?

694
00:37:06,150 --> 00:37:08,270
Because I happen to know
where he's rehearsing.

695
00:37:18,830 --> 00:37:23,010
DE LA CRUZ: <i>♪ Remember me
Don't let it make you cry ♪</i>

696
00:37:24,300 --> 00:37:26,570
(SCOFFS) You better have
my dress, Hector.

697
00:37:26,570 --> 00:37:27,950
HECTOR: <i>Hola,</i> Ceci.

698
00:37:29,010 --> 00:37:30,950
(HECTOR YELPS)

699
00:37:32,610 --> 00:37:33,780
♪ ♪

700
00:37:33,780 --> 00:37:38,050
- <i>Hola.</i>
- Ceci, I lost the dress.

701
00:37:38,050 --> 00:37:39,710
<i>Ya lo sabia!</i>

702
00:37:39,720 --> 00:37:41,980
I got to dress
forty dancers by sunrise.

703
00:37:41,990 --> 00:37:45,850
Thanks to you, I'm one Frida
short of an opening number!

704
00:37:45,860 --> 00:37:49,940
Dante!
We shouldn't be in here.

705
00:37:56,000 --> 00:37:57,310
(GASPS)

706
00:38:01,340 --> 00:38:03,190
- (CHITTERING)
- (BARKING)

707
00:38:04,880 --> 00:38:07,190
No, no, Dante! <i>Ven aca!</i>

708
00:38:07,640 --> 00:38:09,060
(GRUNTS)

709
00:38:16,020 --> 00:38:17,890
You! How did you
get in here?

710
00:38:17,890 --> 00:38:22,060
- I just followed my...
- Oh! The mighty Xolo dog!

711
00:38:22,060 --> 00:38:25,030
Guider of wandering spirits.

712
00:38:25,030 --> 00:38:28,060
And whose spirit
have you guided to me?

713
00:38:28,070 --> 00:38:30,430
I don't think
he's a spirit guide.

714
00:38:30,430 --> 00:38:31,430
Ah, ah, ah.

715
00:38:31,440 --> 00:38:34,500
The alebrijes of this world
can take many forms.

716
00:38:34,510 --> 00:38:37,820
They are as mysterious
as they are powerful.

717
00:38:39,380 --> 00:38:40,690
(COUGHS)

718
00:38:43,410 --> 00:38:47,260
Or maybe he's just a dog.
Come, I need your eyes.

719
00:38:48,520 --> 00:38:52,690
You are the audience.
Darkness.

720
00:38:52,690 --> 00:38:56,910
And from the darkness,
a giant papaya.

721
00:38:57,860 --> 00:39:00,860
Dancers emerge
from the papaya,

722
00:39:00,860 --> 00:39:04,930
and the dancers are all me.

723
00:39:04,940 --> 00:39:07,670
And they go to drink from
the milk of their mother,

724
00:39:07,670 --> 00:39:08,870
who is a cactus.

725
00:39:08,870 --> 00:39:10,610
But who is also me.

726
00:39:10,610 --> 00:39:14,920
And her milk is
not milk but tears.

727
00:39:15,880 --> 00:39:16,950
Is it too obvious?

728
00:39:16,950 --> 00:39:20,680
I think it's just
the right amount of obvious?

729
00:39:20,680 --> 00:39:24,080
It could use some music.
Oh, what if you did like...

730
00:39:24,090 --> 00:39:26,090
- (SINGS TUNE)
- (SNAPS FINGERS)

731
00:39:26,090 --> 00:39:27,490
(ALL PLAYING TUNE)

732
00:39:27,490 --> 00:39:28,960
Oh! And then it could go...

733
00:39:28,960 --> 00:39:31,560
(SINGING TUNE)

734
00:39:31,560 --> 00:39:34,560
(PLAYING TUNE)

735
00:39:34,570 --> 00:39:37,430
And what if
everything was on fire?

736
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:39,630
- (GASPS)
- Yes! Fire! Everywhere!

737
00:39:39,640 --> 00:39:43,840
Inspired! You have
the spirit of an artist.

738
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:45,770
(BAND PLAYING)

739
00:39:45,780 --> 00:39:48,710
The dancers exit. The music
fades, the lights go out.

740
00:39:48,710 --> 00:39:52,050
And Ernesto de la Cruz
rises to the stage!

741
00:39:52,050 --> 00:39:53,360
(GASPS)

742
00:39:55,850 --> 00:39:57,150
Huh?

743
00:39:57,150 --> 00:39:59,490
He does a couple of songs, the
sun rises, everyone cheers...

744
00:39:59,490 --> 00:40:02,020
Excuse me,
where's the real de la Cruz?

745
00:40:02,020 --> 00:40:04,120
Ernesto doesn't do
rehearsals!

746
00:40:04,130 --> 00:40:08,040
He's too busy hosting that fancy
party at the top of his tower.

747
00:40:10,200 --> 00:40:11,370
(SIGHS)

748
00:40:11,370 --> 00:40:13,670
<i>Chamaco,</i> you can't run off
on me like that.

749
00:40:13,670 --> 00:40:15,500
Stop pestering
the celebrities.

750
00:40:15,510 --> 00:40:17,670
You said my great-great-grandpa
would be here!

751
00:40:17,670 --> 00:40:20,540
He's halfway across town
throwing some big party.

752
00:40:20,540 --> 00:40:22,950
That bum. Who doesn't show up
to his own rehearsal?

753
00:40:22,950 --> 00:40:25,880
If you're such good friends,
how come he didn't invite you?

754
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:28,750
He's your great-great-grandpa,
how come he didn't invite you?

755
00:40:28,750 --> 00:40:31,750
Hey, Gustavo! You know
anything about this party?

756
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:33,190
(SCOFFS)
It's the hot ticket!

757
00:40:33,190 --> 00:40:34,790
But if you're not
on the guest list,

758
00:40:34,790 --> 00:40:37,230
you're never
getting in, <i>Chorizo.</i>

759
00:40:37,230 --> 00:40:40,030
- Hey! It's <i>Chorizo! Choricito!</i>
- (ALL LAUGHING)

760
00:40:40,030 --> 00:40:41,660
A-ha. Very funny, guys.
Very funny.

761
00:40:41,670 --> 00:40:42,900
<i>Chorizo?</i>

762
00:40:42,900 --> 00:40:45,030
Oh, this guy's famous!

763
00:40:45,030 --> 00:40:47,170
Go on, go on.
Ask him how he died.

764
00:40:47,170 --> 00:40:48,800
I don't want
to talk about it.

765
00:40:48,810 --> 00:40:51,940
He choked on some <i>chorizo!</i>

766
00:40:51,940 --> 00:40:54,040
(ALL LAUGHING)

767
00:40:54,040 --> 00:40:55,780
I didn't choke, okay?

768
00:40:55,780 --> 00:40:57,780
I got food poisoning
which is a big difference.

769
00:40:57,780 --> 00:40:58,910
(ALL LAUGHING)

770
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:00,550
This is why
I don't like musicians.

771
00:41:00,550 --> 00:41:02,180
Bunch of
self-important jerks.

772
00:41:02,190 --> 00:41:04,690
- Hey! I'm a musician!
- You are?

773
00:41:04,690 --> 00:41:07,520
If you really want
to get to Ernesto,

774
00:41:07,530 --> 00:41:08,920
there is that
music competition...

775
00:41:08,930 --> 00:41:10,590
at the Plaza de la Cruz.

776
00:41:10,590 --> 00:41:13,140
Winner gets
to play at his party.

777
00:41:14,100 --> 00:41:17,100
No, no. <i>Chamaco,</i>
you're <i>loco</i> if you think...

778
00:41:17,100 --> 00:41:19,530
I need to get my
great-great-grandfather's blessing!

779
00:41:19,540 --> 00:41:21,420
You know where
I can get a guitar?

780
00:41:22,010 --> 00:41:25,290
(SIGHS) I know a guy.

781
00:41:35,090 --> 00:41:36,820
(SNIFFING)

782
00:41:36,820 --> 00:41:39,950
Have you found him, Pepita?
Have you found our boy?

783
00:41:39,960 --> 00:41:41,160
(BLOWS)

784
00:41:41,160 --> 00:41:43,960
- ROSITA: A footprint!
- It's a Rivera boot.

785
00:41:43,960 --> 00:41:45,830
- Size seven!
- And a half.

786
00:41:45,830 --> 00:41:48,280
- Pronated.
- Miguel.

787
00:41:57,780 --> 00:41:59,710
HECTOR: Why the heck would
you want to be a musician?

788
00:41:59,710 --> 00:42:01,580
MIGUEL: My great-great-grandpa
was a musician!

789
00:42:01,580 --> 00:42:03,110
Who spent his life
performing like a monkey

790
00:42:03,110 --> 00:42:04,910
for complete strangers.

791
00:42:04,920 --> 00:42:07,320
(GROANS) No thank you.
No! <i>Guacala!</i>

792
00:42:07,320 --> 00:42:09,180
(SCOFFS)
What do you know?

793
00:42:09,190 --> 00:42:11,590
So, how far is
this guitar anyway?

794
00:42:11,590 --> 00:42:12,970
We're almost there.

795
00:42:13,290 --> 00:42:15,040
(GROANS)

796
00:42:17,800 --> 00:42:19,380
Keep up, <i>chamaco.</i> Come on.

797
00:42:21,130 --> 00:42:22,980
(HECTOR WHISTLES)

798
00:42:24,870 --> 00:42:27,050
(MUSIC PLAYING)

799
00:42:28,040 --> 00:42:32,740
- ALL: Cousin Hector!
- Hey! These guys! Hey, <i>Tio!</i>

800
00:42:32,740 --> 00:42:33,880
<i>¿Que onda?</i>

801
00:42:33,880 --> 00:42:35,340
These people are
all your family?

802
00:42:35,350 --> 00:42:36,710
Uh...

803
00:42:36,710 --> 00:42:40,050
In a way. We're all the ones
with no photos or <i>ofrendas.</i>

804
00:42:40,050 --> 00:42:43,190
No family to go home to.
Nearly forgotten, you know?

805
00:42:43,190 --> 00:42:47,340
So, we all call each other
cousin, or <i>tio,</i> or whatever.

806
00:42:48,360 --> 00:42:51,760
- (DANTE WHINES)
- (GRUNTING)

807
00:42:51,760 --> 00:42:54,280
- Hector!
- <i>Tia</i> Chelo!

808
00:42:54,630 --> 00:42:56,060
(ALL LAUGHING)

809
00:42:56,070 --> 00:42:58,170
<i>Muchas gracias!</i>

810
00:42:58,170 --> 00:43:00,700
Hey! Save some for me!
Is Chicharron around?

811
00:43:00,700 --> 00:43:01,870
CHELO: Eh, in the bungalow.

812
00:43:01,870 --> 00:43:04,370
I don't know if he's in
the mood for visitors.

813
00:43:04,370 --> 00:43:07,660
(SCOFFS) Who doesn't like
a visit from Cousin Hector?

814
00:43:11,080 --> 00:43:12,960
- (GASPS)
- (CLATTERS)

815
00:43:16,820 --> 00:43:18,690
<i>Buenas noches,</i> Chicharron!

816
00:43:18,690 --> 00:43:21,120
I don't want to see
your stupid face, Hector.

817
00:43:21,130 --> 00:43:23,190
Come on.
It's <i>Dia de Muertos.</i>

818
00:43:23,190 --> 00:43:24,790
I brought you
a little offering.

819
00:43:24,800 --> 00:43:26,860
- Get out of here.
- I would, Cheech.

820
00:43:26,860 --> 00:43:29,510
But the thing is,
me and my friend, Miguel...

821
00:43:30,670 --> 00:43:32,370
We really need
to borrow your guitar.

822
00:43:32,370 --> 00:43:33,940
- My guitar?
- Yes.

823
00:43:33,940 --> 00:43:36,240
My prized beloved guitar?

824
00:43:36,240 --> 00:43:38,070
I promise
we'll bring it right back.

825
00:43:38,070 --> 00:43:40,740
Like the time you promised
to bring back my van?

826
00:43:40,740 --> 00:43:42,210
- Uh...
- Or my mini-fridge?

827
00:43:42,210 --> 00:43:43,950
- Ah, you see...
- Or my good napkins?

828
00:43:43,950 --> 00:43:45,780
My lasso? My femur?

829
00:43:45,780 --> 00:43:47,010
Well, no,
not like those times.

830
00:43:47,020 --> 00:43:49,350
Where is my femur?
You... (GROANING)

831
00:43:49,350 --> 00:43:51,350
Whoa, whoa.

832
00:43:51,360 --> 00:43:55,270
- You okay, <i>amigo?</i>
- (SIGHS) I'm fading, Hector.

833
00:43:55,860 --> 00:43:58,290
I can feel it.

834
00:43:58,300 --> 00:44:01,480
I couldn't even play
that thing if I wanted to.

835
00:44:04,700 --> 00:44:07,240
You play me something.

836
00:44:07,240 --> 00:44:09,300
No. You know
I don't play anymore, Cheech.

837
00:44:09,310 --> 00:44:11,240
The guitar is for the kid.

838
00:44:11,240 --> 00:44:15,020
You want it,
you got to earn it.

839
00:44:16,410 --> 00:44:19,300
<i>Ay,</i> only for you, <i>amigo.</i>

840
00:44:20,380 --> 00:44:21,850
(STRUMMING)

841
00:44:21,850 --> 00:44:23,250
Any requests?

842
00:44:23,250 --> 00:44:27,340
(CHUCKLES)
You know my favorite, Hector.

843
00:44:28,460 --> 00:44:30,440
(PLAYING SOFT MUSIC)

844
00:44:44,810 --> 00:44:48,520
<i>♪ Well,
everyone knows Juanita</i>

845
00:44:49,480 --> 00:44:53,100
<i>♪ Her eyes
each a different color</i>

846
00:44:54,780 --> 00:44:59,470
<i>♪ Her teeth stick out
And her chin goes in</i>

847
00:45:00,420 --> 00:45:03,070
<i>♪ And her...</i>

848
00:45:04,030 --> 00:45:07,160
<i>♪ Knuckles they
drag on the floor</i>

849
00:45:07,160 --> 00:45:09,800
- Those aren't the words.
- There are children present.

850
00:45:09,800 --> 00:45:13,550
<i>♪ Her hair is like a briar</i>

851
00:45:14,510 --> 00:45:18,490
<i>♪ She stands in
a bow-legged stance</i>

852
00:45:20,180 --> 00:45:24,490
<i>♪ And if I weren't so ugly</i>

853
00:45:26,180 --> 00:45:31,700
<i>♪ She'd possibly
give me a chance ♪</i>

854
00:45:35,530 --> 00:45:37,390
(LAUGHS)

855
00:45:37,390 --> 00:45:40,110
Brings back memories.

856
00:45:44,270 --> 00:45:46,250
<i>Gracias.</i>

857
00:45:56,150 --> 00:45:57,830
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

858
00:46:03,890 --> 00:46:05,200
(WHINES)

859
00:46:17,170 --> 00:46:19,500
Wait. What happened?

860
00:46:19,500 --> 00:46:21,540
He's been forgotten.

861
00:46:21,540 --> 00:46:23,100
When there's no one left
in the living world

862
00:46:23,100 --> 00:46:24,440
who remembers you...

863
00:46:24,440 --> 00:46:27,240
you disappear
from this world.

864
00:46:27,240 --> 00:46:30,180
We call it
the final death.

865
00:46:30,180 --> 00:46:32,380
(STAMMERS) Where did he go?

866
00:46:32,380 --> 00:46:33,650
No one knows.

867
00:46:33,650 --> 00:46:37,850
But I've met him. I could
remember him when I go back!

868
00:46:37,860 --> 00:46:40,190
No, it doesn't work
like that, <i>chamaco.</i>

869
00:46:40,190 --> 00:46:43,160
Our memories,
they have to be passed down

870
00:46:43,160 --> 00:46:44,990
by those
who knew us in life...

871
00:46:45,000 --> 00:46:48,860
in the stories
they tell about us.

872
00:46:48,870 --> 00:46:51,710
But there's no one left alive
to pass down Cheech's stories.

873
00:46:54,040 --> 00:46:56,200
Hey, it happens
to everyone eventually.

874
00:46:56,210 --> 00:46:59,190
Come on, de la Cruzcito,
you've got a contest to win.

875
00:47:11,290 --> 00:47:13,290
MIGUEL: You told me
you hated musicians.

876
00:47:13,290 --> 00:47:14,590
You never said you were one.

877
00:47:14,590 --> 00:47:17,060
HECTOR: How do you think I
knew your great-great-grandpa?

878
00:47:17,060 --> 00:47:18,290
We used to play
music together.

879
00:47:18,300 --> 00:47:20,260
Taught him
everything he knows.

880
00:47:20,260 --> 00:47:23,530
<i>No manches!</i> You played
with Ernesto de la Cruz...

881
00:47:23,530 --> 00:47:25,430
the greatest musician
of all time?

882
00:47:25,430 --> 00:47:27,200
(LAUGHS) Ah, you're funny.

883
00:47:27,200 --> 00:47:29,170
Greatest eyebrows
of all time maybe.

884
00:47:29,170 --> 00:47:31,170
But his music?
Eh, not so much.

885
00:47:31,170 --> 00:47:33,360
You don't know
what you're talking about.

886
00:47:35,310 --> 00:47:38,280
HECTOR: Welcome
to the Plaza de la Cruz!

887
00:47:38,280 --> 00:47:40,530
Showtime, <i>chamaco!</i>

888
00:47:44,050 --> 00:47:46,550
(WHOOPING)

889
00:47:46,560 --> 00:47:49,940
<i>Llevelo!</i>
T-shirts! Bobbleheads!

890
00:47:50,630 --> 00:47:52,540
(ALL CHEERING)

891
00:47:54,330 --> 00:47:56,200
(ALL GASP)

892
00:47:56,200 --> 00:47:59,940
<i>Bienvenidos a todos!</i>

893
00:47:59,940 --> 00:48:01,940
Oh! (LAUGHS)

894
00:48:01,940 --> 00:48:06,470
- Who's ready for some <i>musica?</i>
- (ALL CHEERING)

895
00:48:06,480 --> 00:48:09,110
It's a battle
of the bands, <i>amigos.</i>

896
00:48:09,110 --> 00:48:12,180
The winner gets to play
for the maestro himself,

897
00:48:12,180 --> 00:48:14,220
Ernesto de la Cruz...

898
00:48:14,220 --> 00:48:17,050
at his <i>fiesta</i> tonight!

899
00:48:17,050 --> 00:48:18,590
That's our ticket, <i>muchacho.</i>

900
00:48:18,590 --> 00:48:20,720
Oh! Oh, oh, oh!

901
00:48:20,720 --> 00:48:23,630
Let the competition begin!

902
00:48:23,630 --> 00:48:25,060
(ALL CHEERING)

903
00:48:25,060 --> 00:48:28,440
(ALL PLAYING UPBEAT MUSIC)

904
00:48:34,670 --> 00:48:36,100
(ALL BARKING)

905
00:48:36,110 --> 00:48:37,790
(PLAYING ACCORDIONS)

906
00:48:40,140 --> 00:48:42,210
So, what's the plan?
What are you gonna play?

907
00:48:42,210 --> 00:48:43,610
Definitely <i>Remember Me.</i>

908
00:48:43,610 --> 00:48:45,010
No! Not that one. No.

909
00:48:45,010 --> 00:48:47,080
Come on.
It's his most popular song!

910
00:48:47,080 --> 00:48:48,380
Ah, it's too popular.

911
00:48:48,380 --> 00:48:50,490
<i>♪ Remember me
Though I have to travel far ♪</i>

912
00:48:50,490 --> 00:48:51,650
<i>♪ Remember me... ♪</i>

913
00:48:51,650 --> 00:48:53,650
<i>♪ Don't let it
make you cry... ♪</i>

914
00:48:53,660 --> 00:48:55,540
(PLAYING <I>REMEMBER ME)</i>

915
00:48:57,090 --> 00:48:58,230
(STAMMERING)

916
00:48:58,230 --> 00:49:01,660
- What about <i>Poco Loco?</i>
- <i>Epa!</i> Now that's a song!

917
00:49:01,670 --> 00:49:03,570
De la Cruzcito?
You're on standby.

918
00:49:03,570 --> 00:49:05,580
Los Chachalacos,
you're up next.

919
00:49:06,770 --> 00:49:08,670
ALL: Los Chachalacos!

920
00:49:08,670 --> 00:49:11,420
- (PLAYING UPBEAT MUSIC)
- (ALL CHEERING)

921
00:49:19,780 --> 00:49:21,780
You always this nervous
before a performance?

922
00:49:21,780 --> 00:49:25,120
I don't know. (SIGHS)
I've never performed before.

923
00:49:25,120 --> 00:49:27,050
What? You said
you were a musician!

924
00:49:27,060 --> 00:49:29,020
(STAMMERS) I am!
I mean, I will be.

925
00:49:29,030 --> 00:49:30,420
- <i>Ay!</i>
- Once I win.

926
00:49:30,430 --> 00:49:33,030
That's your plan?
No. You have to win.

927
00:49:33,030 --> 00:49:34,600
Your life
literally depends on...

928
00:49:34,600 --> 00:49:36,160
you winning. And you've
never done this before!

929
00:49:36,170 --> 00:49:37,330
I'll go up there.

930
00:49:37,330 --> 00:49:39,670
- No! I need to do this.
- Why?

931
00:49:39,670 --> 00:49:42,140
If I can't go out
and play one song,

932
00:49:42,140 --> 00:49:44,040
