It's just... (SIGHS)

1166
01:02:39,450 --> 01:02:41,850
I have been looking up to you
my whole life.

1167
01:02:41,850 --> 01:02:45,230
You're the guy
who actually did it!

1168
01:02:46,190 --> 01:02:49,120
But did you ever regret it?

1169
01:02:49,130 --> 01:02:52,540
Choosing music
over everything else?

1170
01:02:52,960 --> 01:02:54,490
It was hard.

1171
01:02:54,500 --> 01:02:58,550
Saying goodbye to my hometown.
Heading off on my own...

1172
01:02:59,500 --> 01:03:01,500
Leaving your family?

1173
01:03:01,500 --> 01:03:06,410
<i>Si.</i> But I could not have
done it differently.

1174
01:03:06,410 --> 01:03:10,010
One cannot deny
who one is meant to be.

1175
01:03:10,010 --> 01:03:14,430
And you, my great-great-grandson,
are meant to be a musician!

1176
01:03:16,850 --> 01:03:19,350
You and I,
we are artists, Miguel.

1177
01:03:19,360 --> 01:03:21,360
We cannot
belong to one family.

1178
01:03:21,360 --> 01:03:23,840
The world is our family.

1179
01:03:25,260 --> 01:03:28,280
Ooh! Ooh!
The fireworks have begun!

1180
01:03:38,540 --> 01:03:43,010
Soon the party will move across
town for my Sunrise Spectacular.

1181
01:03:43,010 --> 01:03:45,980
(GASPS) Miguel,
you must come to the show!

1182
01:03:45,980 --> 01:03:48,010
You will be
my guest of honor!

1183
01:03:48,020 --> 01:03:50,430
- You mean it?
- Of course, my boy.

1184
01:03:52,120 --> 01:03:54,290
(SIGHING) I can't.

1185
01:03:54,290 --> 01:03:56,990
I have to get home
before sunrise.

1186
01:03:56,990 --> 01:03:59,310
Oh! I really do
need to get you home.

1187
01:04:03,300 --> 01:04:06,160
It has been an honor.

1188
01:04:06,170 --> 01:04:08,570
I am sorry
to see you go, Miguel.

1189
01:04:08,570 --> 01:04:10,450
I hope you die very soon.

1190
01:04:12,070 --> 01:04:14,660
(CHUCKLES)
You know what I mean.

1191
01:04:16,680 --> 01:04:19,480
Miguel, I give you my bless...

1192
01:04:19,480 --> 01:04:21,550
HECTOR:
We had a deal, <i>chamaco.</i>

1193
01:04:21,550 --> 01:04:25,180
Who are you?
What is the meaning of this?

1194
01:04:25,190 --> 01:04:28,020
Oh, Frida! I thought
you couldn't make it.

1195
01:04:28,020 --> 01:04:30,190
You said
you'd take back my photo.

1196
01:04:30,190 --> 01:04:31,590
You promised, Miguel.

1197
01:04:31,590 --> 01:04:33,630
You know this, uh, man?

1198
01:04:33,630 --> 01:04:37,380
Uh, I just met him tonight.
He told me he knew you.

1199
01:04:37,600 --> 01:04:39,630
(STAMMERS) Hector?

1200
01:04:39,630 --> 01:04:42,920
Please, Miguel.
Put my photo up.

1201
01:04:44,940 --> 01:04:49,080
My friend,
you're being forgotten.

1202
01:04:49,080 --> 01:04:50,710
- And whose fault is that?
- Hector, please...

1203
01:04:50,710 --> 01:04:53,510
Those were my songs you took.
My songs that made you famous.

1204
01:04:53,520 --> 01:04:54,580
What?

1205
01:04:54,580 --> 01:04:56,210
If I'm being forgotten,
it's because you never

1206
01:04:56,220 --> 01:04:58,090
told anyone
that I wrote them!

1207
01:04:58,090 --> 01:05:01,320
That's crazy! De la Cruz
wrote all his own songs.

1208
01:05:01,320 --> 01:05:03,220
You want to tell him
or should I?

1209
01:05:03,230 --> 01:05:05,630
Hector, I never meant
to take credit.

1210
01:05:05,630 --> 01:05:09,200
We made a great team,
but you died...

1211
01:05:09,200 --> 01:05:11,230
and I only sang your songs

1212
01:05:11,230 --> 01:05:14,230
because I wanted to keep
a part of you alive.

1213
01:05:14,240 --> 01:05:15,970
Oh, how generous!

1214
01:05:15,970 --> 01:05:18,200
You really did
play together.

1215
01:05:18,210 --> 01:05:20,540
I don't want
to fight about it.

1216
01:05:20,540 --> 01:05:22,380
I just want you
to make it right.

1217
01:05:22,380 --> 01:05:26,430
Miguel can put my photo up, and
I can cross over the bridge.

1218
01:05:27,250 --> 01:05:29,150
I can see my girl.

1219
01:05:29,150 --> 01:05:32,120
Ernesto,
remember the night I left?

1220
01:05:32,120 --> 01:05:33,650
That was a long time ago.

1221
01:05:33,660 --> 01:05:35,290
We drank together
and you told me

1222
01:05:35,290 --> 01:05:37,260
you would move
Heaven and Earth...

1223
01:05:37,260 --> 01:05:41,230
for your <i>amigo.</i>
Well, I'm asking you to now.

1224
01:05:41,230 --> 01:05:43,530
Heaven and Earth?
Like in the movie?

1225
01:05:43,530 --> 01:05:46,270
- What?
- That's Don Hidalgo's toast.

1226
01:05:46,270 --> 01:05:48,770
In the de la Cruz movie,
<i>El Camino a Casa.</i>

1227
01:05:48,770 --> 01:05:50,170
I'm talking about
my real life, Miguel.

1228
01:05:50,170 --> 01:05:53,010
No! It's in there. Look!

1229
01:05:53,010 --> 01:05:54,380
DON: (ON TV) <i>Never were
truer words spoken.</i>

1230
01:05:54,380 --> 01:05:57,540
<i>This calls for a toast.
To our friendship!</i> (LAUGHS)

1231
01:05:57,550 --> 01:06:00,250
<i>I would move Heaven and Earth
for you,</i> mi amigo.

1232
01:06:00,250 --> 01:06:03,380
But in the movie, Don
Hidalgo poisons the drink.

1233
01:06:03,390 --> 01:06:06,340
- DON: Salud!
- DE LA CRUZ: <i>Poison!</i>

1234
01:06:08,290 --> 01:06:12,790
That night, Ernesto.
The night I left...

1235
01:06:12,800 --> 01:06:15,400
<i>We'd been performing
on the road for months.</i>

1236
01:06:15,400 --> 01:06:16,700
<i>I got homesick...</i>

1237
01:06:16,700 --> 01:06:18,480
<i>and I packed up my songs.</i>

1238
01:06:19,030 --> 01:06:20,070
You want to give up now

1239
01:06:20,070 --> 01:06:22,540
when we're this close
to reaching our dream?

1240
01:06:22,540 --> 01:06:24,570
This was your dream.
You'll manage.

1241
01:06:24,570 --> 01:06:26,570
I can't do this
without your songs, Hector.

1242
01:06:26,570 --> 01:06:27,740
I'm going home, Ernesto.

1243
01:06:27,740 --> 01:06:30,490
Hate me if you want,
but my mind is made up.

1244
01:06:32,280 --> 01:06:33,550
(DOOR OPENS)

1245
01:06:33,550 --> 01:06:36,820
Oh, I could never hate you.
If you must go,

1246
01:06:36,820 --> 01:06:39,930
then I'm sending you off
with a toast.

1247
01:06:43,490 --> 01:06:44,760
To our friendship.

1248
01:06:44,760 --> 01:06:49,380
I would move Heaven and Earth
for you, <i>mi amigo. Salud!</i>

1249
01:06:53,700 --> 01:06:55,470
HECTOR: <i>You walked me
to the train station.</i>

1250
01:06:55,470 --> 01:06:58,340
<i>But I felt
a pain in my stomach.</i>

1251
01:06:58,340 --> 01:07:00,610
<i>I thought it must have been
something I ate.</i>

1252
01:07:00,610 --> 01:07:03,110
Perhaps it was
that <i>chorizo,</i> my friend.

1253
01:07:03,110 --> 01:07:05,660
HECTOR:
<i>Or something I drank.</i>

1254
01:07:09,090 --> 01:07:10,930
<i>I woke up dead.</i>

1255
01:07:12,520 --> 01:07:14,790
You poisoned me.

1256
01:07:14,790 --> 01:07:18,320
You're confusing movies
with reality, Hector.

1257
01:07:18,330 --> 01:07:21,980
All this time, I thought
it was just bad luck.

1258
01:07:23,360 --> 01:07:27,080
HECTOR: <i>I never thought that
you might have... That you...</i>

1259
01:07:28,470 --> 01:07:30,870
- (YELLS)
- (GROANS)

1260
01:07:30,870 --> 01:07:32,740
- How could you?
- Hector!

1261
01:07:32,740 --> 01:07:34,090
Security! Security!

1262
01:07:34,740 --> 01:07:38,830
You took everything
away from me! You rat!

1263
01:07:39,780 --> 01:07:43,350
Have him taken care of.
He's not well.

1264
01:07:43,350 --> 01:07:48,140
I just wanted to go back home.
No! No!

1265
01:07:49,290 --> 01:07:52,630
(PANTING) I apologize.
Where were we?

1266
01:07:52,630 --> 01:07:54,830
You were going to give me
your blessing.

1267
01:07:54,830 --> 01:07:57,480
Yes. Uh, <i>si.</i>

1268
01:08:00,400 --> 01:08:04,240
Miguel, uh,
my reputation...

1269
01:08:04,240 --> 01:08:07,710
(CHUCKLES) It is
very important to me.

1270
01:08:07,710 --> 01:08:09,810
I would hate
to have you think...

1271
01:08:09,810 --> 01:08:13,850
That you murdered Hector
for his songs?

1272
01:08:13,850 --> 01:08:15,280
(LAUGHS)

1273
01:08:15,280 --> 01:08:18,580
You don't think that.
Do you?

1274
01:08:18,590 --> 01:08:23,570
(STAMMERS) I... No. Everyone
knows you're the good guy.

1275
01:08:29,800 --> 01:08:32,880
<i>Papa</i> Ernesto, my blessing?

1276
01:08:34,840 --> 01:08:39,610
Security? Take care of Miguel.
He'll be extending his stay.

1277
01:08:39,610 --> 01:08:42,740
What? But I'm your family!

1278
01:08:42,750 --> 01:08:45,310
And Hector
was my best friend.

1279
01:08:45,310 --> 01:08:48,710
Success doesn't
come for free, Miguel.

1280
01:08:48,720 --> 01:08:50,880
You have to be willing to do
whatever it takes

1281
01:08:50,890 --> 01:08:54,350
- to seize your moment.
- (GASPS)

1282
01:08:54,360 --> 01:08:55,940
I know you understand.

1283
01:08:56,320 --> 01:08:58,870
No! No!

1284
01:08:59,190 --> 01:09:00,560
(GRUNTING)

1285
01:09:00,560 --> 01:09:03,500
Let go! No!

1286
01:09:03,500 --> 01:09:05,510
(SCREAMING)

1287
01:09:09,210 --> 01:09:11,690
(GASPS AND COUGHS)

1288
01:09:25,920 --> 01:09:30,260
(ECHOING) Help!
Can anyone hear me?

1289
01:09:30,260 --> 01:09:32,710
I want to go home.

1290
01:09:32,860 --> 01:09:35,510
(PANTING)

1291
01:09:47,380 --> 01:09:49,120
- (RUSTLING)
- (GASPS)

1292
01:09:51,250 --> 01:09:52,910
- (STAMMERS) Hector?
- Kid?

1293
01:09:52,920 --> 01:09:55,780
Oh, Hector!
You were right.

1294
01:09:55,780 --> 01:09:58,380
I should have gone
back to my family.

1295
01:09:58,390 --> 01:10:00,950
They told me not
to be like de la Cruz,

1296
01:10:00,960 --> 01:10:02,790
but I didn't listen.

1297
01:10:02,790 --> 01:10:05,790
I told them I didn't care
if they remembered me.

1298
01:10:05,790 --> 01:10:09,360
I didn't care if I was
on their stupid <i>ofrenda.</i>

1299
01:10:09,360 --> 01:10:12,270
Hey, <i>chamaco.</i>
It's okay. It's okay.

1300
01:10:12,270 --> 01:10:14,880
I told them I didn't care.

1301
01:10:16,940 --> 01:10:18,570
(GASPING)

1302
01:10:18,570 --> 01:10:21,760
Hector! Hector?

1303
01:10:22,440 --> 01:10:25,680
She's forgetting me.

1304
01:10:25,680 --> 01:10:28,960
- Who?
- My daughter.

1305
01:10:31,390 --> 01:10:35,820
She's the reason you wanted
to cross the bridge.

1306
01:10:35,820 --> 01:10:39,330
I just wanted
to see her again.

1307
01:10:39,330 --> 01:10:42,010
I never should have
left Santa Cecilia.

1308
01:10:43,060 --> 01:10:45,060
I wish I could apologize.

1309
01:10:45,070 --> 01:10:49,070
I wish I could tell her that her
<i>papa</i> was trying to come home.

1310
01:10:49,070 --> 01:10:51,650
That he loved her so much.

1311
01:10:53,980 --> 01:10:55,890
My Coco...

1312
01:10:57,810 --> 01:10:59,630
Coco?

1313
01:11:15,500 --> 01:11:18,830
Where did you get this?

1314
01:11:18,830 --> 01:11:22,650
That's my <i>Mama</i> Coco.
That's my <i>Mama</i> Imelda.

1315
01:11:23,600 --> 01:11:26,690
Is that you?

1316
01:11:30,350 --> 01:11:33,830
- We're...
- BOTH: Family?

1317
01:11:46,030 --> 01:11:48,730
HECTOR: I always hoped
I'd see her again.

1318
01:11:48,730 --> 01:11:51,130
That she'd miss me.

1319
01:11:51,130 --> 01:11:55,220
Maybe put up my photo.
But it never happened.

1320
01:11:56,370 --> 01:11:58,500
You know the worst part?

1321
01:11:58,510 --> 01:12:00,770
Even if I never got to see
Coco in the living world...

1322
01:12:00,770 --> 01:12:04,380
I thought at least
one day I'd see her here.

1323
01:12:04,380 --> 01:12:06,090
Give her the biggest hug.

1324
01:12:08,050 --> 01:12:11,880
But she's the last person
who remembers me.

1325
01:12:11,890 --> 01:12:14,150
The moment she's gone
from the living world...

1326
01:12:14,160 --> 01:12:18,060
You disappear...
from this one.

1327
01:12:18,060 --> 01:12:19,930
You'll never get to see her.

1328
01:12:19,930 --> 01:12:21,940
Ever again.

1329
01:12:24,930 --> 01:12:28,070
You know,
I wrote her a song once.

1330
01:12:28,070 --> 01:12:32,070
We used to sing it every
night at the same time.

1331
01:12:32,070 --> 01:12:34,820
No matter
how far apart we were.

1332
01:12:35,780 --> 01:12:38,440
What I wouldn't give
to sing it to her

1333
01:12:38,450 --> 01:12:41,400
one... last... time.

1334
01:12:43,420 --> 01:12:47,120
<i>♪ Remember me</i>

1335
01:12:47,120 --> 01:12:51,970
<i>♪ Though I have to say
goodbye Remember me</i>

1336
01:12:52,930 --> 01:12:55,960
<i>♪ Don't let it make you cry</i>

1337
01:12:55,960 --> 01:13:01,830
<i>♪ For even if I'm far away
I hold you in my heart</i>

1338
01:13:01,840 --> 01:13:07,790
<i>♪ I sing a secret song to
you Each night we are apart</i>

1339
01:13:08,710 --> 01:13:11,080
<i>♪ Remember me</i>

1340
01:13:11,080 --> 01:13:12,410
<i>Papa!</i>

1341
01:13:12,410 --> 01:13:16,760
<i>♪ Though I have to
travel far Remember me</i>

1342
01:13:17,620 --> 01:13:21,550
<i>♪ Each time
you hear a sad guitar</i>

1343
01:13:21,560 --> 01:13:27,440
<i>♪ Know that I'm with you
The only way that I can be</i>

1344
01:13:29,600 --> 01:13:34,080
<i>♪ Until you're in
my arms again</i>

1345
01:13:36,000 --> 01:13:42,760
<i>♪ Remember me ♪</i>

1346
01:13:48,520 --> 01:13:52,620
He stole your guitar.
He stole your songs.

1347
01:13:52,620 --> 01:13:56,250
You should be the one the world
remembers, not de la Cruz!

1348
01:13:56,260 --> 01:13:59,030
I didn't write <i>Remember Me</i>
for the world.

1349
01:13:59,030 --> 01:14:00,940
I wrote it for Coco.

1350
01:14:02,630 --> 01:14:05,630
I'm a pretty sorry excuse
for a great-great-grandpa.

1351
01:14:05,630 --> 01:14:08,900
Are you kidding? A minute ago I
thought I was related to a murderer.

1352
01:14:08,900 --> 01:14:11,170
You're a total upgrade.

1353
01:14:11,170 --> 01:14:13,810
My whole life,
there's been something...

1354
01:14:13,810 --> 01:14:15,540
that made me different.

1355
01:14:15,540 --> 01:14:17,830
And I never knew
where it came from.

1356
01:14:18,650 --> 01:14:22,180
But now I know.
It comes from you.

1357
01:14:22,180 --> 01:14:27,050
I'm proud we're family!
I'm proud to be his family!

1358
01:14:27,060 --> 01:14:28,800
(WHOOPING)

1359
01:14:30,930 --> 01:14:33,380
(WHOOPING)

1360
01:14:34,060 --> 01:14:36,830
I'm proud to be
his family!

1361
01:14:36,830 --> 01:14:39,670
(WHOOPING)

1362
01:14:39,670 --> 01:14:41,880
(ECHOING)

1363
01:14:47,240 --> 01:14:49,960
(DANTE HOWLING)

1364
01:14:51,780 --> 01:14:53,680
Dante?

1365
01:14:53,680 --> 01:14:56,110
- (BARKS)
- Dante!

1366
01:14:56,120 --> 01:14:58,130
(BARKING)

1367
01:14:58,690 --> 01:15:00,270
It's Dante!

1368
01:15:02,120 --> 01:15:03,510
(ROARS)

1369
01:15:04,990 --> 01:15:06,310
(LAUGHS)

1370
01:15:06,560 --> 01:15:09,010
(LAUGHING)

1371
01:15:11,870 --> 01:15:15,150
- Imelda!
- Hector.

1372
01:15:15,570 --> 01:15:17,150
You look good.

1373
01:15:22,740 --> 01:15:24,990
(WHIMPERS)

1374
01:15:26,980 --> 01:15:28,320
(ROARS)

1375
01:15:28,320 --> 01:15:31,580
Dante! You knew he was my
<i>Papa</i> Hector the whole time!

1376
01:15:31,590 --> 01:15:33,590
You are a real spirit guide.

1377
01:15:33,590 --> 01:15:36,120
Who's the good spirit guide?
You are!

1378
01:15:36,120 --> 01:15:37,360
(LAUGHS)

1379
01:15:37,360 --> 01:15:40,070
(WHINING)

1380
01:15:43,130 --> 01:15:44,450
(GASPS)

1381
01:15:47,030 --> 01:15:48,350
Whoa!

1382
01:15:50,840 --> 01:15:52,450
- (LAUGHS)
- (BARKS)

1383
01:15:55,740 --> 01:15:57,290
Dante!

1384
01:15:57,750 --> 01:15:59,290
(GASPS)

1385
01:16:00,150 --> 01:16:02,060
(BARKING)

1386
01:16:09,720 --> 01:16:12,170
(ROARS)

1387
01:16:20,940 --> 01:16:22,240
There they are!

1388
01:16:22,240 --> 01:16:26,590
ALL: Miguel! Miguelito! Look, it's Miguel!
He's all right.

1389
01:16:28,040 --> 01:16:31,090
<i>Gracias, Dios mio.
Que bueno.</i>

1390
01:16:31,310 --> 01:16:32,630
(GROANS)

1391
01:16:34,350 --> 01:16:36,100
(SCOFFS)

1392
01:16:37,890 --> 01:16:39,370
(BARKS)

1393
01:16:42,690 --> 01:16:43,920
(YELPS)

1394
01:16:43,930 --> 01:16:45,190
(CHUCKLES)

1395
01:16:45,190 --> 01:16:47,230
<i>Mijo,</i> I was so worried!

1396
01:16:47,230 --> 01:16:49,480
Thank goodness
we found you in time.

1397
01:16:50,430 --> 01:16:53,970
And you... How many times
must I turn you away?

1398
01:16:53,970 --> 01:16:55,230
Imelda.

1399
01:16:55,240 --> 01:16:58,440
I want nothing to do with you!
Not in life, not in death!

1400
01:16:58,440 --> 01:17:02,080
I spent decades protecting
my family from your mistakes.

1401
01:17:02,080 --> 01:17:04,080
He spends
five minutes with you

1402
01:17:04,080 --> 01:17:05,810
and I have to fish him
out of a sinkhole!

1403
01:17:05,810 --> 01:17:07,350
I wasn't in there
because of Hector.

1404
01:17:07,350 --> 01:17:09,980
He was in there
because of me.

1405
01:17:09,980 --> 01:17:12,250
He was just
trying to get me home!

1406
01:17:12,250 --> 01:17:16,720
I didn't want to listen,
but he was right.

1407
01:17:16,720 --> 01:17:19,010
Nothing's more
important than family.

1408
01:17:19,960 --> 01:17:22,640
I'm ready
to accept your blessing.

1409
01:17:23,060 --> 01:17:25,100
And your conditions.

1410
01:17:25,100 --> 01:17:27,400
But first,
I need to find de la Cruz.

1411
01:17:27,400 --> 01:17:29,270
To get Hector's photo.

1412
01:17:29,270 --> 01:17:30,970
- What?
- So he can see Coco again.

1413
01:17:30,970 --> 01:17:32,870
Hector should be
on our <i>ofrenda.</i>

1414
01:17:32,870 --> 01:17:34,340
He's part of our family.

1415
01:17:34,340 --> 01:17:35,810
He left this family!

1416
01:17:35,810 --> 01:17:37,480
He tried to go home
to you and Coco.

1417
01:17:37,480 --> 01:17:39,460
But de la Cruz
murdered him!

1418
01:17:40,420 --> 01:17:42,260
It's true, Imelda.

1419
01:17:43,020 --> 01:17:44,480
And so what if it's true?

1420
01:17:44,490 --> 01:17:46,990
You leave me alone
with a child to raise...

1421
01:17:46,990 --> 01:17:49,090
and I'm just
supposed to forgive you?

1422
01:17:49,090 --> 01:17:51,020
Imelda, I... (GROANS)

1423
01:17:51,030 --> 01:17:53,260
- Hector!
- (GASPS)

1424
01:17:53,260 --> 01:17:54,860
(BREATHES SHAKILY)

1425
01:17:54,860 --> 01:17:58,610
I'm running out of time.
It's Coco.

1426
01:17:59,770 --> 01:18:01,450
She's forgetting you.

1427
01:18:02,400 --> 01:18:05,240
You don't have
to forgive him.

1428
01:18:05,240 --> 01:18:07,560
But we shouldn't
forget him.

1429
01:18:09,980 --> 01:18:13,380
I wanted to forget you.

1430
01:18:13,380 --> 01:18:16,280
I wanted Coco
to forget you too, but...

1431
01:18:16,280 --> 01:18:19,330
This is my fault.
Not yours.

1432
01:18:21,390 --> 01:18:23,540
I'm sorry, Imelda.

1433
01:18:27,430 --> 01:18:31,160
Miguel, if we help you
get his photo,

1434
01:18:31,170 --> 01:18:32,900
you will return home?

1435
01:18:32,900 --> 01:18:34,480
No more music?

1436
01:18:35,440 --> 01:18:38,090
Family comes first.

1437
01:18:39,770 --> 01:18:43,220
I can't forgive you.

1438
01:18:45,450 --> 01:18:47,400
But I will help you.

1439
01:18:48,350 --> 01:18:51,330
So, how do we get
to de la Cruz?

1440
01:18:52,290 --> 01:18:55,100
I might know a way.

1441
01:18:56,930 --> 01:18:59,370
(DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING)

1442
01:19:05,200 --> 01:19:08,350
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

1443
01:19:10,470 --> 01:19:12,290
♪ ♪

1444
01:19:19,810 --> 01:19:21,230
(MUSIC STOPS)

1445
01:19:23,320 --> 01:19:25,370
(SPOOKY MUSIC PLAYING)

1446
01:19:45,510 --> 01:19:48,120
- Good luck, <i>muchacho.</i>
- <i>Gracias,</i> Frida.

1447
01:19:49,210 --> 01:19:51,560
(ALL GRUNTING)

1448
01:19:52,980 --> 01:19:54,850
- (SCREAMS IN PAIN)
- (YELPS)

1449
01:19:54,850 --> 01:19:56,620
(PANTING)

1450
01:19:56,620 --> 01:19:59,890
- Here, let me help you with...
- Don't touch me!

1451
01:19:59,890 --> 01:20:02,160
- Everyone clear on the plan?
- Find Hector's photo.

1452
01:20:02,160 --> 01:20:03,990
- Give it to Miguel.
- Send Miguel home.

1453
01:20:03,990 --> 01:20:05,840
- Got your petals?
- (BARKS)

1454
01:20:06,860 --> 01:20:08,490
Now, we just
have to find de la Cruz.

1455
01:20:08,500 --> 01:20:09,810
- Yes?
- (SCREAMS)

1456
01:20:10,630 --> 01:20:12,580
Don't I know you?

1457
01:20:13,430 --> 01:20:16,170
That's for murdering
the love of my life!

1458
01:20:16,170 --> 01:20:18,240
- Who... Who the...
- She's talking about me!

1459
01:20:18,240 --> 01:20:19,540
I'm the love of your life?

1460
01:20:19,540 --> 01:20:21,310
I don't know.
I'm still angry at you.

1461
01:20:21,310 --> 01:20:22,640
Hector!
How did you... (GROANS)

1462
01:20:22,640 --> 01:20:25,580
And that's for trying
to murder my grandson.

1463
01:20:25,580 --> 01:20:27,980
- Grandson?
- She's talking about me!

1464
01:20:27,980 --> 01:20:32,150
You! Wait.
You're related to Hector?

1465
01:20:32,150 --> 01:20:33,700
The photo!

1466
01:20:35,420 --> 01:20:37,060
Uh...

1467
01:20:37,060 --> 01:20:38,770
After him!

1468
01:20:39,530 --> 01:20:40,930
(GROANS)

1469
01:20:40,930 --> 01:20:43,130
Security! <i>Ayudenme!</i>

1470
01:20:43,130 --> 01:20:46,200
- You said love of your life.
- I don't know what I said.

1471
01:20:46,200 --> 01:20:47,620
That's what I heard.

1472
01:20:49,900 --> 01:20:52,190
(GRUNTING)

1473
01:21:00,920 --> 01:21:02,900
Places, <i>Senor.</i>
You're on in thirty seconds.

1474
01:21:04,150 --> 01:21:06,270
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1475
01:21:07,190 --> 01:21:08,670
- (MAMA IMELDA YELPS)
- (GASPS)

1476
01:21:09,460 --> 01:21:12,370
- (GRUNTS)
- <i>Ay!</i> Miguel! I have it!

1477
01:21:12,590 --> 01:21:13,910
(YELPS)

1478
01:21:15,460 --> 01:21:17,510
- (RUMBLING)
- (YELPS)

1479
01:21:21,070 --> 01:21:22,380
Oh!

1480
01:21:25,470 --> 01:21:26,890
(SCREAMS)

1481
01:21:28,310 --> 01:21:29,920
MIGUEL: Hurry! Come on!

1482
01:21:31,310 --> 01:21:33,610
EMCEE: <i>Ladies and gentlemen...</i>

1483
01:21:33,610 --> 01:21:39,480
<i>the one... the only...
Ernesto de la Cruz!</i>

1484
01:21:39,490 --> 01:21:42,840
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

1485
01:21:48,400 --> 01:21:49,630
Get her off the stage.

1486
01:21:49,630 --> 01:21:52,380
(PANTING)

1487
01:21:56,240 --> 01:21:58,340
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1488
01:21:58,340 --> 01:22:01,390
Sing! Sing!

1489
01:22:07,110 --> 01:22:11,800
<i>♪ Ay, de mi Llorona</i>

1490
01:22:12,750 --> 01:22:17,440
<i>♪ Llorona de azul celeste</i>

1491
01:22:20,390 --> 01:22:24,030
<i>♪ Ay, de mi Llorona</i>

1492
01:22:24,030 --> 01:22:25,260
(AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

1493
01:22:25,270 --> 01:22:29,680
<i>♪ Llorona de azul celeste</i>

1494
01:22:31,640 --> 01:22:36,610
<i>♪ Y aunque la vida
me cueste, Llorona</i>

1495
01:22:36,610 --> 01:22:44,380
<i>♪ No dejare de quererte</i>

1496
01:22:44,390 --> 01:22:46,530
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

1497
01:22:47,390 --> 01:22:50,790
<i>♪ Me subi al pino mas alto,
Llorona</i>

1498
01:22:50,790 --> 01:22:53,460
<i>♪ A ver si te divisaba</i>

1499
01:22:53,460 --> 01:22:58,200
<i>♪ Como el pino era tierno,
Llorona</i>

1500
01:22:58,200 --> 01:23:01,330
<i>♪ Al verme llorar, lloraba</i>

1501
01:23:01,340 --> 01:23:08,570
<i>♪ Ay de mi Llorona, Llorona
Llorona de azul celeste</i>

1502
01:23:08,580 --> 01:23:15,480
<i>♪ Ay de mi Llorona, Llorona
Llorona de azul celeste</i>

1503
01:23:15,480 --> 01:23:19,480
<i>♪ Y aunque la vida
me cueste, Llorona</i>

1504
01:23:19,490 --> 01:23:22,820
<i>♪ No dejare de quererte</i>

1505
01:23:22,820 --> 01:23:24,090
Let go of me!

1506
01:23:24,090 --> 01:23:26,790
<i>♪ Y aunque la vida
me cueste, Llorona</i>

1507
01:23:26,800 --> 01:23:38,490
<i>♪ No dejare de quererte</i>

1508
01:23:38,740 --> 01:23:41,620
<i>♪ Ay, ay, ay ♪</i>

1509
01:23:42,710 --> 01:23:44,680
(GROANING)

1510
01:23:44,680 --> 01:23:47,060
(AUDIENCE CHEERING)

1511
01:23:47,480 --> 01:23:49,730
(LAUGHING)

1512
01:23:50,390 --> 01:23:52,450
I forgot
what that felt like.

1513
01:23:52,450 --> 01:23:55,070
You still got it.

1514
01:23:56,090 --> 01:23:58,740
- (MIGUEL CLEARS THROAT)
- Oh.

1515
01:24:01,260 --> 01:24:04,350
Miguel,
I give you my blessing.

1516
01:24:05,530 --> 01:24:09,530
To go home,
to put up our photos

1517
01:24:09,540 --> 01:24:11,300
and to never...

1518
01:24:11,310 --> 01:24:13,720
Never play music again.

1519
01:24:14,680 --> 01:24:19,630
To never forget how much
your family loves you.

1520
01:24:21,850 --> 01:24:23,630
You're going home.

1521
01:24:27,150 --> 01:24:29,160
You're not going anywhere.

1522
01:24:29,160 --> 01:24:30,770
(BOTH GRUNTING)

1523
01:24:30,820 --> 01:24:31,890
Imelda!

1524
01:24:31,890 --> 01:24:33,330
DE LA CRUZ: Stay back!
Stay back!

1525
01:24:33,330 --> 01:24:37,560
All of you, stay back.
Not one more step.

1526
01:24:37,560 --> 01:24:39,330
(BARKING)

1527
01:24:39,330 --> 01:24:40,850
Dante!

1528
01:24:41,140 --> 01:24:42,240
(GROANS)

1529
01:24:42,240 --> 01:24:46,540
Ernesto, stop!
Leave the boy alone.

1530
01:24:46,540 --> 01:24:48,470
I've worked too hard, Hector.

1531
01:24:48,470 --> 01:24:50,810
Too hard to let him
destroy everything.

1532
01:24:50,810 --> 01:24:52,880
HECTOR:
He's a living child, Ernesto.

1533
01:24:52,880 --> 01:24:54,480
He's a threat! (ECHOES)

1534
01:24:54,480 --> 01:24:56,320
<i>You think
I'd let him go back</i>

1535
01:24:56,320 --> 01:24:58,320
<i>to the Land of the Living
with your photo?</i>

1536
01:24:58,320 --> 01:25:01,390
To keep
your memory alive? No.

1537
01:25:01,390 --> 01:25:04,260
- You're a coward!
- I am Ernesto de la Cruz.

1538
01:25:04,260 --> 01:25:06,190
The greatest musician
of all time!

1539
01:25:06,190 --> 01:25:08,160
Hector's the real musician.

1540
01:25:08,160 --> 01:25:09,460
<i>You're just the guy
who murdered him</i>

1541
01:25:09,460 --> 01:25:10,700
- <i>and stole his songs!</i>
- (ALL GASP)

1542
01:25:10,700 --> 01:25:11,860
Murdered?

1543
01:25:11,870 --> 01:25:13,800
I am the one
who's willing to do

1544
01:25:13,800 --> 01:25:15,820
what it takes
to seize my moment.

1545
01:25:16,240 --> 01:25:17,950
Whatever it takes.

1546
01:25:18,670 --> 01:25:21,440
- (SCREAMING)
- No!

1547
01:25:21,440 --> 01:25:23,510
(AUDIENCE EXCLAIMING)

1548
01:25:23,510 --> 01:25:25,680
MAMA IMELDA AND OSCAR:
Miguel!

1549
01:25:25,680 --> 01:25:29,430
Apologies, old friend.
But the show must go on.

1550
01:25:30,390 --> 01:25:32,800
(SCREAMING)

1551
01:25:36,420 --> 01:25:38,140
(CONTINUES SCREAMING)

1552
01:25:44,930 --> 01:25:46,980
(CONTINUES SCREAMING)

1553
01:25:52,770 --> 01:25:54,620
(ROARS)

1554
01:26:03,250 --> 01:26:04,930
(INHALES SHARPLY)

1555
01:26:04,990 --> 01:26:06,720
(LAUGHS)

1556
01:26:06,720 --> 01:26:10,570
(AUDIENCE BOOING)

1557
01:26:11,390 --> 01:26:14,260
(LAUGHING) Please,
please, <i>mi familia.</i>

1558
01:26:14,260 --> 01:26:16,330
- MAN: Murderer!
- (AUDIENCE JEERING)

1559
01:26:16,330 --> 01:26:18,830
Orchestra.
A-one, a-two, a-one...

1560
01:26:18,830 --> 01:26:21,330
(AUDIENCE BOOING)

1561
01:26:21,340 --> 01:26:24,600
<i>♪ Remember me
Though I have to s... ♪</i>

1562
01:26:24,610 --> 01:26:25,910
Hey!

1563
01:26:25,910 --> 01:26:27,010
(BOOING CONTINUES)

1564
01:26:27,010 --> 01:26:28,520
Look!

1565
01:26:41,890 --> 01:26:45,140
- (GROWLING)
- (CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

1566
01:26:48,660 --> 01:26:51,030
- Nice kitty.
- (ROARS)

1567
01:26:51,030 --> 01:26:54,270
(SCREAMING)

1568
01:26:54,270 --> 01:26:58,770
Put me down! No, please! I beg of you!
Stop! Stop! No!

1569
01:26:58,770 --> 01:27:00,860
(DE LA CRUZ SCREAMING)

1570
01:27:07,450 --> 01:27:09,060
No! No!

1571
01:27:09,750 --> 01:27:10,880
(CLANGS)

1572
01:27:10,890 --> 01:27:11,980
(GROANS)

1573
01:27:11,990 --> 01:27:13,300
- (CREAKS)
- (GASPS)

1574
01:27:16,520 --> 01:27:19,170
(ALL CHEERING)

1575
01:27:20,600 --> 01:27:21,890
What did I miss?

1576
01:27:21,890 --> 01:27:23,700
Good boy, Dante!

1577
01:27:23,700 --> 01:27:25,010
Miguel!

1578
01:27:25,330 --> 01:27:26,430
(HECTOR GROANS)

1579
01:27:26,430 --> 01:27:30,770
Hector!
The photo... I lost it!

1580
01:27:30,770 --> 01:27:33,710
It's okay, <i>mijo.</i>
It's o... (GROANING)

1581
01:27:33,710 --> 01:27:36,620
Hector! Hector?

1582
01:27:37,510 --> 01:27:38,640
Coco.

1583
01:27:38,650 --> 01:27:41,080
No! We can still
find the photo.

1584
01:27:41,080 --> 01:27:43,030
Miguel, it's almost sunrise.

1585
01:27:43,980 --> 01:27:45,750
No, no. I can't leave you.

1586
01:27:45,750 --> 01:27:48,320
I promised
I'd put your photo up.

1587
01:27:48,320 --> 01:27:50,460
I promised you'd see Coco.

1588
01:27:50,460 --> 01:27:52,840
We're both
out of time, <i>mijo.</i>

1589
01:27:53,800 --> 01:27:57,060
Oh no! No!
She can't forget you!

1590
01:27:57,060 --> 01:28:01,250
I just wanted her to know
that I loved her.

1591
01:28:02,400 --> 01:28:03,470
Hector!

1592
01:28:03,470 --> 01:28:05,790
You have our blessing,
Miguel.

1593
01:28:06,010 --> 01:28:08,540
No conditions.

1594
01:28:08,540 --> 01:28:11,660
No! <i>Papa</i> Hector, please!

1595
01:28:15,520 --> 01:28:16,860
No!

1596
01:28:17,820 --> 01:28:18,990
Go home.

1597
01:28:18,990 --> 01:28:22,200
I promise I won't let Coco forget you!
(SCREAMS)

1598
01:28:37,710 --> 01:28:39,090
(GASPS)

1599
01:28:40,010 --> 01:28:41,720
(PANTING)

1600
01:28:49,080 --> 01:28:50,800
- There he is!
- (GROANS)

1601
01:28:51,820 --> 01:28:53,900
Miguel! Stop!

1602
01:28:55,820 --> 01:28:57,370
(PANTING)

1603
01:28:58,860 --> 01:29:00,430
- Where have you been?
- (GASPS)

1604
01:29:00,430 --> 01:29:02,090
I need to see
<i>Mama</i> Coco, please.

1605
01:29:02,100 --> 01:29:05,160
What are you doing with that...
Give it to me!

1606
01:29:05,170 --> 01:29:08,970
Miguel, stop!
Miguel! Miguel!

1607
01:29:08,970 --> 01:29:10,900
(POUNDING ON DOOR)

1608
01:29:10,900 --> 01:29:15,440
<i>Mama</i> Coco? Can you hear me?
It's Miguel.

1609
01:29:15,440 --> 01:29:20,110
I saw your <i>papa.</i>
Remember? <i>Papa?</i>

1610
01:29:20,110 --> 01:29:26,520
Please! If you forget him,
he'll be gone. Forever.

1611
01:29:26,520 --> 01:29:28,020
PAPA: Miguel,
open this door!

1612
01:29:28,020 --> 01:29:30,860
Here. This was
his guitar, right?

1613
01:29:30,860 --> 01:29:32,340
He used to play it to you?

1614
01:29:35,000 --> 01:29:39,030
See? There he is! <i>Papa!</i>

1615
01:29:39,030 --> 01:29:41,250
Remember? <i>Papa?</i>

1616
01:29:44,670 --> 01:29:45,740
- (KNOCKING ON DOOR)
- PAPA: Miguel!

1617
01:29:45,740 --> 01:29:48,820
<i>Mama</i> Coco, please!
Don't forget him.

1618
01:29:53,110 --> 01:29:55,110
- (KEYS JANGLING)
- (DOOR UNLOCKS)

1619
01:29:55,120 --> 01:29:57,080
What are you doing
to that poor woman?

1620
01:29:57,080 --> 01:29:58,580
It's okay, <i>Mamita.</i>
It's okay.

1621
01:29:58,590 --> 01:29:59,850
PAPA:
What's gotten into you?

1622
01:29:59,850 --> 01:30:01,840
(SOBBING)

1623
01:30:06,530 --> 01:30:08,190
I thought
I'd lost you, Miguel.

1624
01:30:08,200 --> 01:30:09,860
MIGUEL: I'm sorry, <i>Papa.</i>

1625
01:30:09,860 --> 01:30:13,210
We're all together now.
That's what matters.

1626
01:30:13,930 --> 01:30:15,200
MIGUEL: Not all of us.

1627
01:30:15,200 --> 01:30:17,600
It's okay, <i>Mamita.</i>

1628
01:30:17,600 --> 01:30:20,850
Miguel, you apologize
to your <i>Mama</i> Coco.

1629
01:30:22,710 --> 01:30:25,860
- (SNIFFLES) <i>Mama</i> Coco?
- (THUDS)

1630
01:30:30,180 --> 01:30:32,370
Well? Apologize!

1631
01:30:36,060 --> 01:30:38,520
<i>Mama</i> Coco?

1632
01:30:38,520 --> 01:30:42,210
Your <i>papa,</i>
he wanted you to have this.

1633
01:30:42,760 --> 01:30:43,860
(STRUMS GUITAR)

1634
01:30:43,860 --> 01:30:45,800
- (GASPS)
- <i>Mama,</i> wait!

1635
01:30:45,800 --> 01:30:49,980
<i>♪ Remember me</i>

1636
01:30:50,940 --> 01:30:53,900
<i>♪ Though I have
to say goodbye</i>

1637
01:30:53,910 --> 01:30:57,140
<i>♪ Remember me</i>

1638
01:30:57,140 --> 01:30:59,980
<i>♪ Don't let it make you cry</i>

1639
01:30:59,980 --> 01:31:03,750
<i>♪ For even if I'm far away</i>

1640
01:31:03,750 --> 01:31:09,750
<i>♪ I hold you in my heart
I sing a secret song to you</i>

1641
01:31:09,760 --> 01:31:13,240
<i>♪ Each night we are apart</i>

1642
01:31:13,660 --> 01:31:17,660
<i>♪ Remember me</i>

1643
01:31:17,670 --> 01:31:21,600
<i>♪ Though I have
